1
00:00:16,658 --> 00:00:18,243
(light music)

2
00:00:55,572 --> 00:00:57,616
(tense music)

3
00:01:15,759 --> 00:01:18,095
(rapid footsteps approaching)

4
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:20,263
(heavy breathing)

5
00:01:25,519 --> 00:01:27,312
(tense music crescendo)

6
00:01:28,605 --> 00:01:30,273
(traffic humming)

7
00:01:38,782 --> 00:01:41,535
(church bell rings)

8
00:01:41,660 --> 00:01:43,245
(background chatter)

9
00:01:45,622 --> 00:01:47,332
(sinister music)

10
00:01:54,631 --> 00:01:56,425
(elevator announcements)

11
00:01:59,803 --> 00:02:01,138
(heavy door opens)

12
00:02:06,977 --> 00:02:08,812
(quiet chatter)

13
00:02:18,363 --> 00:02:20,782
(music crescendo)

14
00:02:20,907 --> 00:02:22,617
(ominous beat)

15
00:03:24,763 --> 00:03:25,931
(ominous beat)

16
00:03:28,058 --> 00:03:29,267
He is with God.

17
00:03:30,977 --> 00:03:32,854
(ominous music)

18
00:03:41,154 --> 00:03:44,074
(dramatic music)
(sobbing)

19
00:03:58,547 --> 00:04:00,090
(metal scrapes)

20
00:04:05,053 --> 00:04:06,555
(light hammering)

21
00:04:08,932 --> 00:04:10,850
(clang)

22
00:04:11,226 --> 00:04:13,228
(sombre music)

23
00:04:24,990 --> 00:04:27,117
The throne of the Holy See

24
00:04:28,577 --> 00:04:29,577
is vacant.

25
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:33,832
(dramatic music)

26
00:04:51,641 --> 00:04:52,684
Aldo.

27
00:04:52,809 --> 00:04:54,102
(quiet chatter)

28
00:04:56,855 --> 00:04:59,232
Hey, do you think that anybody
would mind

29
00:04:59,357 --> 00:05:02,527
- if I took that, as a keepsake?
- Of course, take it.

30
00:05:02,652 --> 00:05:04,404
He would've wanted you to
have it.

31
00:05:04,529 --> 00:05:07,616
Because we used to play quite often in
the evenings.

32
00:05:07,949 --> 00:05:11,119
He said... it helped him
to relax. (chuckles)

33
00:05:11,244 --> 00:05:12,370
And who won?

34
00:05:12,495 --> 00:05:13,495
- Oh, he did.
- (laughs)

35
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:15,248
He was always eight moves ahead.

36
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:17,917
Hmm.

37
00:05:18,043 --> 00:05:19,043
Aldo...

38
00:05:19,753 --> 00:05:20,837
I'm sorry.

39
00:05:20,962 --> 00:05:21,962
Hmm.

40
00:05:22,339 --> 00:05:25,258
No, go on. What happened,
do you know?

41
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:28,094
No. They say a heart attack,
but...

42
00:05:28,803 --> 00:05:30,263
there had been warnings.

43
00:05:30,388 --> 00:05:32,015
I don't know.
I hadn't heard that.

44
00:05:32,140 --> 00:05:34,309
Yeah. He didn't want anyone
to know.

45
00:05:35,185 --> 00:05:36,770
He was afraid that if word
got out

46
00:05:36,895 --> 00:05:39,606
that they would start
circulating rumours

47
00:05:39,731 --> 00:05:41,316
that he was going to resign.

48
00:05:43,401 --> 00:05:44,401
The Curia.

49
00:05:45,570 --> 00:05:47,197
(ominous music)
Yes.

50
00:05:49,574 --> 00:05:50,574
Okay.

51
00:06:00,794 --> 00:06:02,879
I know this is hard for you,
but...

52
00:06:03,004 --> 00:06:05,632
we will have to prepare a detailed statement.

53
00:06:07,759 --> 00:06:09,844
Who discovered
the Holy Father's body?

54
00:06:11,721 --> 00:06:13,098
I did, Your Eminence.

55
00:06:13,223 --> 00:06:14,891
And then what did you do?

56
00:06:17,227 --> 00:06:20,605
I... called the Holy Father's
doctor.

57
00:06:20,730 --> 00:06:21,856
Mm-hmm.

58
00:06:21,981 --> 00:06:23,483
But it was too late.

59
00:06:23,608 --> 00:06:24,608
Mm-hmm.

60
00:06:24,943 --> 00:06:26,486
And what time was this?

61
00:06:27,904 --> 00:06:31,199
Around... 11:30, Eminence.

62
00:06:32,742 --> 00:06:34,786
We would have called you
earlier, but...

63
00:06:38,456 --> 00:06:41,000
Thomas, I'm so sorry.

64
00:06:41,126 --> 00:06:43,795
I know His Holiness had
no colleagues

65
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,588
closer than you and Aldo.

66
00:06:46,464 --> 00:06:49,134
But I asked Janusz to hold off
calling you.

67
00:06:49,259 --> 00:06:52,262
I wanted to ascertain
all the facts.

68
00:06:52,679 --> 00:06:55,181
You know how rumour spreads.

69
00:06:55,306 --> 00:07:00,311
I've prepared a timeline of
His Holiness's last day,

70
00:07:01,146 --> 00:07:06,568
and these are the Holy Father's
most recent medical records.

71
00:07:06,693 --> 00:07:09,696
And who was the last to have
a scheduled meeting with him?

72
00:07:09,821 --> 00:07:11,239
I believe that may have been me.

73
00:07:11,364 --> 00:07:13,074
Father Wozniak,
I was the last one?

74
00:07:13,199 --> 00:07:15,285
You were, Eminence Tremblay.

75
00:07:16,035 --> 00:07:18,121
Put in all the meetings he had
that day.

76
00:07:19,205 --> 00:07:22,333
It will show how hard he was
working right to the very end.

77
00:07:22,459 --> 00:07:23,459
Well...

78
00:07:24,169 --> 00:07:26,337
it might look like we
were placing

79
00:07:26,463 --> 00:07:28,715
a huge burden on a sick man.

80
00:07:29,132 --> 00:07:30,842
The Papacy is a huge burden,

81
00:07:31,301 --> 00:07:32,927
especially for an older man.

82
00:07:34,512 --> 00:07:35,847
(tense beat)

83
00:07:37,974 --> 00:07:39,434
Well, Dean,

84
00:07:39,559 --> 00:07:41,728
it seems the responsibility for the Conclave

85
00:07:41,853 --> 00:07:42,853
falls upon you.

86
00:07:42,937 --> 00:07:44,814
(sombre music)

87
00:08:03,166 --> 00:08:04,542
(in Italian): Seal the room.

88
00:08:05,043 --> 00:08:06,294
(dramatic music)

89
00:08:07,879 --> 00:08:09,589
(zipping)

90
00:08:14,677 --> 00:08:16,221
(high tempo music)
(gurney clanking)

91
00:08:19,808 --> 00:08:21,059
(straps pulling)

92
00:08:29,859 --> 00:08:30,944
(light switch clicks)

93
00:08:35,365 --> 00:08:36,366
(door closes)

94
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:50,421
(gurney wheels trundling)

95
00:09:09,983 --> 00:09:11,317
(siren blares)

96
00:09:19,409 --> 00:09:21,536
(quiet, rhythmic clacking)

97
00:09:39,637 --> 00:09:41,890
(lively street sounds)

98
00:09:42,015 --> 00:09:43,659
(in English): Security say they'd like to test

99
00:09:43,683 --> 00:09:45,578
the electronic jammers
one last time, Your Eminence.

100
00:09:45,602 --> 00:09:46,787
Well, then they'd better
be quick.

101
00:09:46,811 --> 00:09:48,605
Is this really necessary, Willi?

102
00:09:49,397 --> 00:09:50,565
Apparently so.

103
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:52,400
They say eavesdroppers
can use lasers

104
00:09:52,525 --> 00:09:54,068
to read the vibrations
of the glass.

105
00:09:54,193 --> 00:09:55,754
Really? Well, let's hope none of our brothers

106
00:09:55,778 --> 00:09:56,988
suffer from claustrophobia.

107
00:09:57,113 --> 00:09:59,240
And who knows how long we're going to be in here?

108
00:09:59,365 --> 00:10:01,868
Can you reassure me that we
will be finished on time?

109
00:10:01,993 --> 00:10:03,888
They will work through
the night if they have to.

110
00:10:03,912 --> 00:10:06,289
It will be fine, Your Eminence.
It always is.

111
00:10:06,414 --> 00:10:08,875
- Italy, you know.
- I'm sorry to fuss.

112
00:10:10,335 --> 00:10:13,379
Well, Eminence, I'd say this is
a pretty fair vision of hell.

113
00:10:13,504 --> 00:10:14,923
Well, don't be blasphemous, Ray.

114
00:10:15,048 --> 00:10:16,174
Hell arrives tomorrow

115
00:10:16,299 --> 00:10:17,717
when we bring in the cardinals.

116
00:10:18,843 --> 00:10:20,428
Now, how do I pronounce this?

117
00:10:22,138 --> 00:10:23,723
Kahl-koh, Your Eminence.
He's Indian.

118
00:10:23,848 --> 00:10:25,141
Oh, Kahl-koh, thank you.

119
00:10:27,602 --> 00:10:32,315
Archbishop Wozniak has asked if
he might have a word, Eminence.

120
00:10:32,982 --> 00:10:34,209
Well, I don't think that's
possible.

121
00:10:34,233 --> 00:10:35,873
The cardinals will be arriving
in an hour.

122
00:10:35,985 --> 00:10:37,820
- What's it about?
- He didn't say.

123
00:10:38,363 --> 00:10:39,723
I... I wouldn't have
brought it up,

124
00:10:39,822 --> 00:10:43,076
it's just he seemed so... upset.

125
00:10:43,201 --> 00:10:45,179
Ray, we're going to be
sequestered from six o'clock.

126
00:10:45,203 --> 00:10:46,388
He should've come to me earlier.

127
00:10:46,412 --> 00:10:47,892
Yes, Your Eminence.
I'll let him know.

128
00:10:49,290 --> 00:10:50,375
No, Ray...

129
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:51,834
tell him that I will see him

130
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:53,378
after I've met the cardinals.

131
00:10:53,503 --> 00:10:54,503
The poor fellow will be

132
00:10:54,587 --> 00:10:56,172
worrying about his future.

133
00:10:56,547 --> 00:10:58,007
(whirring, buzzing)

134
00:11:04,222 --> 00:11:05,848
(quiet prayers whispered)

135
00:11:12,939 --> 00:11:15,066
(distant traffic rumbling)

136
00:11:17,860 --> 00:11:19,112
(footsteps echoing)

137
00:11:23,449 --> 00:11:24,609
(distant tannoy announcement)

138
00:11:33,251 --> 00:11:34,460
(ominous music)

139
00:11:39,298 --> 00:11:40,800
(high tempo music)

140
00:11:51,310 --> 00:11:52,895
(helicopter whirring)

141
00:11:53,021 --> 00:11:54,021
(men chattering)

142
00:11:59,318 --> 00:12:00,653
(laughing)

143
00:12:34,604 --> 00:12:36,022
(high tempo music continues)

144
00:12:51,704 --> 00:12:53,456
So, how many is that, Willi?

145
00:12:53,581 --> 00:12:55,416
103, Eminence Lawrence.

146
00:12:55,958 --> 00:12:57,960
I wonder where Tedesco
has got to.

147
00:12:58,086 --> 00:12:59,170
Perhaps he's not coming.

148
00:12:59,295 --> 00:13:00,922
Well, that'd be too much
to hope for.

149
00:13:01,047 --> 00:13:03,466
(chuckling)

150
00:13:03,591 --> 00:13:04,985
We could wait inside,
if you prefer.

151
00:13:05,009 --> 00:13:06,849
No, let's stay out here and get some fresh air

152
00:13:06,969 --> 00:13:07,970
while we can.

153
00:13:08,096 --> 00:13:09,096
Ah.

154
00:13:12,183 --> 00:13:13,518
Father Bellini.

155
00:13:13,643 --> 00:13:14,977
(echoing footsteps)

156
00:13:15,103 --> 00:13:16,187
Aldo.

157
00:13:17,563 --> 00:13:19,857
- Am I the last?
- Not quite. How are you?

158
00:13:19,982 --> 00:13:22,568
Oh, well, you know,
fairly dreadful.

159
00:13:23,069 --> 00:13:24,505
- Have you seen the papers?
- Mm-hmm.

160
00:13:24,529 --> 00:13:26,215
Apparently it's already decided
it's to be me.

161
00:13:26,239 --> 00:13:27,865
And I happen to agree with them.

162
00:13:28,199 --> 00:13:30,576
(scoffs) What if I don't
want it?

163
00:13:31,035 --> 00:13:32,620
No sane man would want
the Papacy.

164
00:13:32,745 --> 00:13:35,623
Some of our colleagues seem to
want it.

165
00:13:35,748 --> 00:13:38,543
What if I know in my heart that
I am not worthy?

166
00:13:38,668 --> 00:13:40,211
You are more worthy than any
of us.

167
00:13:40,336 --> 00:13:41,814
- I'm not.
- Well, then tell your supporters

168
00:13:41,838 --> 00:13:44,549
not to vote for you.
Pass the chalice.

169
00:13:44,674 --> 00:13:46,134
And let it go to him?

170
00:13:46,467 --> 00:13:48,094
I could never live with myself.

171
00:13:48,219 --> 00:13:49,762
(helicopter whirring)

172
00:13:51,013 --> 00:13:52,473
(in Italian): Eminence Tedesco.

173
00:13:52,598 --> 00:13:53,808
(laughter)

174
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:55,393
Dean Lawrence!

175
00:13:56,227 --> 00:13:57,270
How are you?

176
00:13:57,395 --> 00:13:58,688
I'm well, Goffredo.

177
00:13:59,689 --> 00:14:01,809
(in English): Sorry, my train
was delayed from Venice.

178
00:14:01,899 --> 00:14:03,568
- (in Italian): We've missed you.
- Yes.

179
00:14:03,693 --> 00:14:04,735
No doubt.

180
00:14:05,403 --> 00:14:08,739
(in English): But don't worry,
my friends have kept me well informed.

181
00:14:08,865 --> 00:14:09,945
(in Italian): Are you well?

182
00:14:10,992 --> 00:14:12,869
(in English): No one is ever well at our age.

183
00:14:12,994 --> 00:14:14,245
(in Italian): True.

184
00:14:14,954 --> 00:14:16,289
(in English): And you, huh?

185
00:14:16,414 --> 00:14:17,915
How do you feel with your new,

186
00:14:18,040 --> 00:14:20,334
er, responsibility?

187
00:14:20,459 --> 00:14:21,919
(uneasy laugh)

188
00:14:23,838 --> 00:14:25,006
Everything under control?

189
00:14:25,131 --> 00:14:26,316
(in Italian): Yes, I believe so.

190
00:14:26,340 --> 00:14:27,717
- Eminence Tedesco, may I?
- No.

191
00:14:29,218 --> 00:14:30,344
(in English): See you later.

192
00:14:30,469 --> 00:14:32,589
(in Italian): You're welcome.
See you later, Eminence.

193
00:14:37,018 --> 00:14:38,269
(plastic rustling)

194
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:42,607
(in English): Tell you what, that's enormous.

195
00:14:42,732 --> 00:14:44,650
Apparently Pope John the 23rd
was too fat

196
00:14:44,775 --> 00:14:46,655
to fit into the biggest cassock, so they had to

197
00:14:46,736 --> 00:14:48,112
split the seam at the back

198
00:14:48,237 --> 00:14:49,530
for him to get into it.

199
00:14:49,906 --> 00:14:51,032
(chuckling)

200
00:14:52,575 --> 00:14:53,659
No.

201
00:14:56,245 --> 00:14:57,538
You look tired.

202
00:14:58,581 --> 00:15:00,166
Well, all this is...

203
00:15:00,791 --> 00:15:02,960
a duty I thought I'd never have
to perform.

204
00:15:03,085 --> 00:15:05,129
I thought he would outlive
all of us.

205
00:15:07,715 --> 00:15:09,800
We didn't part well.

206
00:15:13,304 --> 00:15:17,266
I asked for his permission to
resign as Dean,

207
00:15:18,517 --> 00:15:19,810
join an order.

208
00:15:20,603 --> 00:15:21,604
What did he say?

209
00:15:22,271 --> 00:15:24,065
He refused my resignation.

210
00:15:24,190 --> 00:15:26,067
Said some were chosen to
be shepherds

211
00:15:26,192 --> 00:15:29,237
and some to manage the farm.

212
00:15:29,362 --> 00:15:31,197
Apparently I am a manager.

213
00:15:31,322 --> 00:15:32,322
(laughs softly)

214
00:15:33,741 --> 00:15:35,743
He told me about your
crisis of faith.

215
00:15:38,371 --> 00:15:41,916
But you should know that he had
his own doubts...

216
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:43,751
towards the end.

217
00:15:43,876 --> 00:15:46,587
Wow, the Pope had doubts
about God?

218
00:15:46,712 --> 00:15:47,712
No.

219
00:15:48,256 --> 00:15:50,633
Never about God.

220
00:15:50,758 --> 00:15:52,802
What he had lost faith in was
the church.

221
00:15:54,303 --> 00:15:55,805
(door creaks opens)
Father Wozniak?

222
00:15:55,930 --> 00:15:57,181
(loud chatter)

223
00:15:57,306 --> 00:15:58,808
In the name of the Father, the Son,

224
00:15:58,933 --> 00:16:00,101
and the Holy Ghost.

225
00:16:00,226 --> 00:16:01,666
- My last confession was...
- Janusz.

226
00:16:01,727 --> 00:16:02,853
- four weeks ago.
- Janusz,

227
00:16:02,979 --> 00:16:03,979
I haven't got time

228
00:16:04,063 --> 00:16:05,147
to hear your confession.

229
00:16:05,273 --> 00:16:06,899
There's still so much to do.

230
00:16:08,276 --> 00:16:09,276
Have you been drinking?

231
00:16:12,238 --> 00:16:13,698
What's troubling you? Tell me.

232
00:16:15,491 --> 00:16:17,076
I should have come to you
before,

233
00:16:18,619 --> 00:16:20,413
but I promised not to
say anything.

234
00:16:20,538 --> 00:16:21,538
Promised who?

235
00:16:21,580 --> 00:16:22,999
Cardinal Tremblay.

236
00:16:23,124 --> 00:16:25,418
Janusz, the doors close soon
and you'll have to leave.

237
00:16:25,543 --> 00:16:27,128
Now, if you promised
Cardinal Tremblay,

238
00:16:27,253 --> 00:16:28,855
then perhaps it isn't
right that you're...

239
00:16:28,879 --> 00:16:30,381
The day the Pope died,

240
00:16:30,756 --> 00:16:33,342
the last person to have
an official appointment with him

241
00:16:33,467 --> 00:16:35,553
- was Cardinal Tremblay.
- Yes, I know,

242
00:16:35,678 --> 00:16:37,805
- it's on the official timeline.
- At that meeting,

243
00:16:37,930 --> 00:16:39,598
the Holy Father dismissed him.

244
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:42,643
What?

245
00:16:42,768 --> 00:16:44,186
He sacked him!

246
00:16:47,231 --> 00:16:48,231
Why?

247
00:16:49,025 --> 00:16:50,568
For gross misconduct.

248
00:16:52,737 --> 00:16:54,447
And you tell me this now?

249
00:16:55,072 --> 00:16:56,741
We're about to be sequestered,
Janusz.

250
00:16:56,866 --> 00:16:59,869
Forgive me, but it wasn't until
the last few days

251
00:16:59,994 --> 00:17:01,454
when I started to hear
the rumours.

252
00:17:01,579 --> 00:17:02,621
What rumours?

253
00:17:02,747 --> 00:17:04,832
That he may be elected Pope.

254
00:17:04,957 --> 00:17:07,877
Oh, and you see it as your duty
to prevent that, do you?

255
00:17:08,002 --> 00:17:10,880
I... I no longer know what my duty is.

256
00:17:24,602 --> 00:17:26,645
Were you there at this meeting?

257
00:17:26,771 --> 00:17:28,147
No, Your Eminence.

258
00:17:28,522 --> 00:17:31,025
The Holy Father told me about
it afterwards,

259
00:17:31,150 --> 00:17:32,318
when we had supper.

260
00:17:32,777 --> 00:17:34,236
Did he tell you why

261
00:17:34,362 --> 00:17:36,072
he had dismissed
Eminence Tremblay?

262
00:17:36,447 --> 00:17:38,032
Err... no.

263
00:17:39,158 --> 00:17:42,828
He said the reasons would
become clear soon enough.

264
00:17:45,164 --> 00:17:46,164
(dramatic music)

265
00:17:46,248 --> 00:17:47,249
(echoing footsteps)

266
00:17:48,626 --> 00:17:54,465
(doors grind, clang closed)

267
00:17:57,468 --> 00:17:59,428
(shutters clang, trundle)

268
00:18:12,525 --> 00:18:14,193
(shutters clang shut)

269
00:18:22,701 --> 00:18:24,203
(steam hissing)

270
00:18:28,082 --> 00:18:29,542
(terrines boiling)

271
00:18:29,667 --> 00:18:30,960
(quiet chatter)

272
00:18:42,304 --> 00:18:43,639
(cutlery clinking)

273
00:19:02,908 --> 00:19:04,577
(nuns talking)

274
00:19:04,702 --> 00:19:05,953
Dean Lawrence...

275
00:19:06,871 --> 00:19:07,871
an issue.

276
00:19:08,873 --> 00:19:10,082
Oh, dear God.

277
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:12,293
- One of them's died?
- I'm sorry?

278
00:19:12,418 --> 00:19:13,794
Have we lost a cardinal?

279
00:19:13,919 --> 00:19:14,920
No, Your Eminence.

280
00:19:15,045 --> 00:19:16,797
We seem to have acquired one.

281
00:19:16,922 --> 00:19:18,090
I mean it literally.

282
00:19:18,215 --> 00:19:20,968
Another cardinal has just
turned up.

283
00:19:21,093 --> 00:19:23,304
Well, then, we've left someone
off the list.

284
00:19:23,429 --> 00:19:26,182
He was never on our list,
Eminence.

285
00:19:26,307 --> 00:19:28,476
He says he was created
in pectore.

286
00:19:28,601 --> 00:19:30,769
Oh no, then he has to be
an imposter, surely.

287
00:19:30,895 --> 00:19:32,372
Well, that's what I thought,
Eminence.

288
00:19:32,396 --> 00:19:34,273
But Archbishop Mandorff has
spoken to him

289
00:19:34,398 --> 00:19:35,858
and he thinks not.

290
00:19:37,651 --> 00:19:39,278
Er, what's this I'm hearing?

291
00:19:41,739 --> 00:19:43,949
His name is Vincent Benitez,
Your Eminence.

292
00:19:44,366 --> 00:19:46,118
He's the Archbishop of Kabul.

293
00:19:46,494 --> 00:19:48,162
Archbishop of where?

294
00:19:48,287 --> 00:19:49,330
Kabul.

295
00:19:49,455 --> 00:19:50,831
But he's Mexican.

296
00:19:51,332 --> 00:19:53,167
The Holy Father appointed him
last year.

297
00:19:53,292 --> 00:19:56,462
Last year? So, how has this
been kept a secret for so long?

298
00:19:56,587 --> 00:19:58,707
I thought perhaps you would be aware of
his elevation.

299
00:19:58,756 --> 00:20:01,509
No, I'm not. Ray, ask
Eminence Bellini to join us,

300
00:20:01,634 --> 00:20:03,177
maybe he knows something
of this.

301
00:20:03,302 --> 00:20:04,929
- Yes, Eminence.
- Thank you.

302
00:20:05,054 --> 00:20:07,348
He has a letter of appointment from the Pope,

303
00:20:07,473 --> 00:20:09,725
addressed to the
archdiocese of Kabul,

304
00:20:09,850 --> 00:20:12,102
which they kept secret at
the Holy Father's request.

305
00:20:12,228 --> 00:20:13,228
Mm-hmm.

306
00:20:14,813 --> 00:20:16,815
You don't think he could've
forged it?

307
00:20:17,566 --> 00:20:19,568
Well, err, where is he now?

308
00:20:21,570 --> 00:20:23,572
BELLINI: A cardinal in
Afghanistan?

309
00:20:23,697 --> 00:20:25,257
- LAWRENCE: Hmm.
- BELLINI: It's absurd.

310
00:20:25,282 --> 00:20:27,034
How many Catholics are there
in Afghanistan?

311
00:20:27,159 --> 00:20:28,970
LAWRENCE: He was head of
the Catholic mission there

312
00:20:28,994 --> 00:20:30,496
until his elevation.

313
00:20:31,497 --> 00:20:33,457
But how can we possibly ensure
his safety?

314
00:20:33,582 --> 00:20:35,584
Well, presumably that's why
the Holy Father

315
00:20:35,709 --> 00:20:37,086
wanted it kept a secret.

316
00:20:37,211 --> 00:20:40,005
Well, it won't be in
pectore now.

317
00:20:40,130 --> 00:20:42,925
I don't think we have any
choice but to admit him.

318
00:20:43,050 --> 00:20:45,052
Wait, wait. Thomas.

319
00:20:47,513 --> 00:20:48,889
Are we sure...

320
00:20:49,014 --> 00:20:51,350
that the Holy Father
was entirely...

321
00:20:51,475 --> 00:20:53,102
competent...

322
00:20:53,227 --> 00:20:54,687
when he made this appointment?

323
00:20:57,314 --> 00:20:58,314
(stutters)

324
00:21:00,150 --> 00:21:04,113
I believe this man is legally
a cardinal, Aldo, and I...

325
00:21:04,530 --> 00:21:07,491
I think he has a right
to take part in the election.

326
00:21:26,594 --> 00:21:28,304
(loud clanging)
(chatter)

327
00:21:30,973 --> 00:21:32,266
(knife clinks on glass)

328
00:21:34,518 --> 00:21:36,145
Eminences, before we eat,

329
00:21:36,270 --> 00:21:39,773
I'd like to introduce a new
member of our order,

330
00:21:40,232 --> 00:21:43,402
whose existence
was not known to any of us

331
00:21:43,527 --> 00:21:45,738
erm, until only a few hours ago.

332
00:21:45,863 --> 00:21:47,865
This is because our brother

333
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:52,328
was made a cardinal by the
perfectly legitimate procedure

334
00:21:52,453 --> 00:21:55,497
known as creation in pectore.

335
00:21:56,040 --> 00:21:58,000
Now, the reason why it had to
be done this way

336
00:21:58,125 --> 00:22:01,337
is known only to God and to
the late Holy Father.

337
00:22:01,462 --> 00:22:02,942
But I think we can guess well enough,

338
00:22:03,047 --> 00:22:05,257
as our new brother's ministry

339
00:22:05,382 --> 00:22:07,551
is an extremely dangerous one.

340
00:22:08,427 --> 00:22:10,304
Welcome to our order,

341
00:22:10,429 --> 00:22:12,264
Vincent Benitez,

342
00:22:12,389 --> 00:22:14,808
Cardinal Archbishop of...

343
00:22:14,933 --> 00:22:15,934
Kabul.

344
00:22:17,227 --> 00:22:18,562
(quiet chatter)

345
00:22:18,687 --> 00:22:21,231
(applause)

346
00:22:32,660 --> 00:22:35,245
Eminence, please would you
bless our meal?

347
00:22:35,371 --> 00:22:37,247
Of course.
(chairs scrape)

348
00:22:39,124 --> 00:22:41,001
Bless us, oh Lord,

349
00:22:41,543 --> 00:22:43,128
and these, your gifts,

350
00:22:43,253 --> 00:22:45,214
which we are about to receive from your bounty.

351
00:22:45,339 --> 00:22:46,382
ALL: Amen.

352
00:22:46,507 --> 00:22:47,675
(men chattering)

353
00:22:48,467 --> 00:22:50,135
(in Spanish): Bless all those

354
00:22:51,261 --> 00:22:54,640
who cannot share this meal
with us

355
00:22:55,015 --> 00:22:58,352
and help us, O Lord,
as we wat and drink,

356
00:22:58,477 --> 00:23:00,187
to remember the hungry,

357
00:23:01,313 --> 00:23:02,398
the thirsty,

358
00:23:03,565 --> 00:23:05,109
the sick,

359
00:23:05,234 --> 00:23:07,027
and the lonely,

360
00:23:07,152 --> 00:23:09,947
and the sisters who prepared
this food for us.

361
00:23:10,864 --> 00:23:12,241
Through Christ Our Lord.

362
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:14,201
Amen.

363
00:23:16,161 --> 00:23:17,204
(in English): Amen.

364
00:23:17,329 --> 00:23:19,206
Please, come.
(loud chatter)

365
00:23:19,331 --> 00:23:20,332
This is your...

366
00:23:31,385 --> 00:23:32,386
(in Italian): Dean!

367
00:23:37,933 --> 00:23:39,059
Goffredo.

368
00:23:39,184 --> 00:23:40,185
Thomas.

369
00:23:40,310 --> 00:23:41,310
(laughs)

370
00:23:41,729 --> 00:23:42,729
Come.

371
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:45,023
(in English): Take some wine.

372
00:23:45,149 --> 00:23:46,316
(wine pouring)

373
00:23:47,735 --> 00:23:48,736
(in Italian): Thank you.

374
00:23:53,323 --> 00:23:54,563
(in English): You look anxious.

375
00:23:54,658 --> 00:23:55,658
Oh...

376
00:23:56,410 --> 00:23:58,203
(in Italian): And we haven't
even begun yet.

377
00:23:58,328 --> 00:23:59,328
(laughs)

378
00:24:01,165 --> 00:24:02,434
(in English): Our new brother...

379
00:24:02,458 --> 00:24:04,418
(in Italian): Did I hear correctly, Afghanistan?

380
00:24:04,543 --> 00:24:05,543
Yes.

381
00:24:05,586 --> 00:24:09,465
A marvellous testament to
the Universal Church,

382
00:24:11,008 --> 00:24:13,427
So many men of different
cultures, races,

383
00:24:13,552 --> 00:24:16,054
bound together
by their faith in God.

384
00:24:17,347 --> 00:24:18,515
(snorts with laughter)

385
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:19,640
Hmm?

386
00:24:21,268 --> 00:24:22,268
Look around you.

387
00:24:23,812 --> 00:24:26,398
Notice how everyone gravitates
to their fellow countrymen.

388
00:24:27,608 --> 00:24:28,942
Italians over here.

389
00:24:29,485 --> 00:24:30,486
Spanish speakers there,

390
00:24:30,611 --> 00:24:31,445
Mm-hmm.

391
00:24:31,570 --> 00:24:32,404
English there.

392
00:24:32,529 --> 00:24:33,529
Yes.

393
00:24:33,822 --> 00:24:34,698
French.

394
00:24:34,823 --> 00:24:35,949
(laughs heartily)

395
00:24:37,034 --> 00:24:38,827
(in English):
Divided by language.

396
00:24:40,496 --> 00:24:43,373
(in Italian): When we were boys
and the Tridentine Mass

397
00:24:43,499 --> 00:24:45,459
was still the only true liturgy
of the world,

398
00:24:46,084 --> 00:24:48,587
we would all have been
speaking Latin.

399
00:24:50,047 --> 00:24:52,883
But then your fellow liberals
insisted we get rid of that

400
00:24:53,008 --> 00:24:54,259
"dead" language.

401
00:24:54,384 --> 00:24:55,384
(chuckles)

402
00:24:57,054 --> 00:24:59,723
Without Rome, without
the tradition of Rome...

403
00:25:02,518 --> 00:25:04,228
(in English): Things fall apart.

404
00:25:05,312 --> 00:25:06,897
The centre cannot hold.

405
00:25:09,483 --> 00:25:13,278
(in Italian): So what,
the next pope must be Italian?

406
00:25:13,403 --> 00:25:14,403
Why not?

407
00:25:14,446 --> 00:25:17,326
We haven't had an Italian pope for more
than 40 years. 40 years, Tommaso.

408
00:25:21,119 --> 00:25:23,622
Can you seriously imagine
the alternative?

409
00:25:23,997 --> 00:25:25,332
(cardinals laughing, chatting)

410
00:25:34,174 --> 00:25:38,637
Excuse me, I must circulate
amongst our brothers.

411
00:25:40,806 --> 00:25:43,433
The abyss calls out.

412
00:25:48,647 --> 00:25:50,527
(in English): It was shrewd of him to stay away

413
00:25:50,566 --> 00:25:52,067
from Rome until today.

414
00:25:52,943 --> 00:25:55,070
One outspoken newspaper
interview

415
00:25:55,195 --> 00:25:56,780
could have written Tedesco off.

416
00:25:57,990 --> 00:26:01,118
But instead, he will do well
tomorrow, I think.

417
00:26:01,243 --> 00:26:03,036
LAWRENCE: Which means?

418
00:26:03,161 --> 00:26:04,538
SABBADIN: I would say...

419
00:26:04,913 --> 00:26:07,666
he's worth 15 votes
on the first ballet.

420
00:26:07,791 --> 00:26:09,167
LAWRENCE: And Bellini?

421
00:26:09,293 --> 00:26:10,377
(soft music)

422
00:26:13,547 --> 00:26:16,717
BELLINI: Why do I feel like a
cow being priced by the farmer?

423
00:26:16,842 --> 00:26:17,885
SABBADIN: First ballot...

424
00:26:19,887 --> 00:26:22,764
Between 20 and 25.

425
00:26:22,890 --> 00:26:26,727
But it is tomorrow night that
the real work begins.

426
00:26:27,144 --> 00:26:32,441
Somehow we have to get him
a two thirds majority, hmm?

427
00:26:32,566 --> 00:26:34,985
By real work you mean what, exactly?

428
00:26:35,110 --> 00:26:38,405
LANDOLFI: But Eminence Bellini, those who seek
the Papacy...

429
00:26:38,530 --> 00:26:41,491
I don't "seek" the Papacy. I...
(doors rattle open)

430
00:26:44,077 --> 00:26:45,245
(cardinal clears his throat)

431
00:26:48,165 --> 00:26:50,334
(metal clanging, rolling)

432
00:26:53,670 --> 00:26:55,005
(in Italian): Thank you, Sisters.

433
00:26:59,593 --> 00:27:00,427
(door closes)

434
00:27:00,552 --> 00:27:02,405
(in English): Listen, you don't
have to do anything.

435
00:27:02,429 --> 00:27:03,889
Just leave it to us.

436
00:27:04,014 --> 00:27:06,892
BELLINI: Tell them I stand for a
common-sense approach

437
00:27:07,225 --> 00:27:11,021
to such issues as gays
and divorce.

438
00:27:11,605 --> 00:27:14,608
Tell them I stand for never
returning to the days

439
00:27:14,733 --> 00:27:16,526
of the Latin liturgy,

440
00:27:17,277 --> 00:27:18,737
or families of ten children

441
00:27:18,862 --> 00:27:21,031
because Mama and Papa
didn't know any better.

442
00:27:21,156 --> 00:27:23,283
That was an ugly
and repressive time

443
00:27:23,408 --> 00:27:24,785
and I'm glad that it's over.

444
00:27:25,285 --> 00:27:26,954
Tell them I stand for...

445
00:27:27,079 --> 00:27:28,580
respecting other faiths,

446
00:27:29,373 --> 00:27:32,542
for tolerating other views
within our own church.

447
00:27:33,794 --> 00:27:36,004
And tell them that I believe

448
00:27:36,129 --> 00:27:38,632
women should play more of
a role in the Curia.

449
00:27:38,757 --> 00:27:39,800
Let's, um...

450
00:27:40,175 --> 00:27:41,802
Let's not mention women.

451
00:27:41,927 --> 00:27:42,927
Why?

452
00:27:43,679 --> 00:27:46,765
Brother, I have no intention of
concealing my views

453
00:27:46,890 --> 00:27:48,809
or pretending to be anything
other than I am

454
00:27:48,934 --> 00:27:51,436
in order to sway any of our
number who are undecided.

455
00:27:51,561 --> 00:27:52,561
So...

456
00:27:53,271 --> 00:27:56,441
if you want to canvas
on my behalf,

457
00:27:56,566 --> 00:27:58,652
then make sure that
my message is clear.

458
00:27:59,319 --> 00:28:03,365
I stand for everything that
Tedesco does not.

459
00:28:07,202 --> 00:28:08,912
- Okay.
- If you'll excuse me.

460
00:28:10,622 --> 00:28:12,457
(footsteps receding)

461
00:28:13,542 --> 00:28:14,793
SABBADIN: Alright.

462
00:28:14,918 --> 00:28:17,629
Rocco, you talk to the Americans.

463
00:28:17,754 --> 00:28:19,881
Villanueva, I'll leave
the South Americans to you.

464
00:28:20,424 --> 00:28:22,926
Gianmarco,
you take the Africans.

465
00:28:23,051 --> 00:28:24,594
Aldo doesn't want it.

466
00:28:25,887 --> 00:28:26,887
Any of it.

467
00:28:28,140 --> 00:28:29,558
You know that, don't you?

468
00:28:29,975 --> 00:28:31,018
SABBADIN: Of course, I do.

469
00:28:31,143 --> 00:28:32,394
That's why I support him.

470
00:28:32,853 --> 00:28:34,438
The men who are dangerous

471
00:28:34,563 --> 00:28:36,440
are the ones who do want it.

472
00:28:37,733 --> 00:28:40,027
(beeping)
(door opens)

473
00:28:45,157 --> 00:28:48,201
I'm enjoying all this mystery,
Thomas.

474
00:28:48,326 --> 00:28:49,327
(door closes)

475
00:28:49,995 --> 00:28:53,790
And I suppose you should tell
me what you want to talk about.

476
00:28:57,085 --> 00:28:59,087
Your last meeting with
the Holy Father.

477
00:29:00,172 --> 00:29:01,214
Oh, what about it?

478
00:29:02,090 --> 00:29:04,009
Well, I've been told
it was difficult.

479
00:29:05,594 --> 00:29:08,555
- Was it?
- TREMBLAY: Difficult? No.

480
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,265
Not that I can recall.

481
00:29:11,099 --> 00:29:12,994
Well, I... I'm sorry to have to
ask you this, Joe,

482
00:29:13,018 --> 00:29:14,019
but to be specific,

483
00:29:14,144 --> 00:29:15,854
I was told that the Holy Father

484
00:29:15,979 --> 00:29:17,355
demanded your resignation.

485
00:29:18,732 --> 00:29:19,732
What?

486
00:29:21,068 --> 00:29:22,527
- That's absurd.
- I...

487
00:29:23,361 --> 00:29:25,614
I don't know what we...
who... who told you that?

488
00:29:25,739 --> 00:29:26,739
Archbishop Wozniak.

489
00:29:26,823 --> 00:29:28,366
Why would he say such a thing?

490
00:29:28,492 --> 00:29:31,411
So, there isn't any truth in the allegation?

491
00:29:31,536 --> 00:29:34,122
Oh God, no, of course not. It's absurd.

492
00:29:34,247 --> 00:29:35,247
Hmm.

493
00:29:35,874 --> 00:29:38,585
- You don't think that...
- No, well, I... I had to ask.

494
00:29:38,710 --> 00:29:40,545
I understand, but no.

495
00:29:40,670 --> 00:29:43,048
You... you can ask
Monsignor Morales.

496
00:29:43,173 --> 00:29:44,424
He was at the meeting.

497
00:29:44,549 --> 00:29:45,342
Well, I would,

498
00:29:45,467 --> 00:29:46,468
but at the moment

499
00:29:46,593 --> 00:29:48,386
we happen to be sequestered.

500
00:29:48,512 --> 00:29:49,512
Oh.

501
00:29:55,185 --> 00:29:57,646
Can you think of any reason why
Archbishop Wozniak

502
00:29:57,771 --> 00:29:59,314
would circulate such a story?

503
00:29:59,439 --> 00:30:01,483
No, I can't.
(coffee machine buzzes)

504
00:30:01,608 --> 00:30:04,277
I really... do you want a coffee?
(coffee machine buzzes)

505
00:30:04,402 --> 00:30:05,402
No.

506
00:30:05,487 --> 00:30:06,567
TREMBLAY: (frustrated sigh)

507
00:30:07,197 --> 00:30:08,365
I'm shocked.

508
00:30:09,574 --> 00:30:10,742
He told you this himself?

509
00:30:10,867 --> 00:30:11,867
Yeah.

510
00:30:17,833 --> 00:30:18,833
You don't think...?

511
00:30:20,544 --> 00:30:21,544
Well, what?

512
00:30:22,671 --> 00:30:23,797
The drinking?

513
00:30:23,922 --> 00:30:26,007
I don't like to bring it up, but we both know

514
00:30:26,133 --> 00:30:29,177
his drinking has been getting
much heavier.

515
00:30:30,011 --> 00:30:34,057
And perhaps it's affecting his
judgement, hi-his mind even.

516
00:30:35,642 --> 00:30:36,810
And...
(sighs)

517
00:30:37,144 --> 00:30:41,148
I know my name has
been mentioned as a future Pope.

518
00:30:41,273 --> 00:30:44,276
And if the Archbishop doesn't
approve of that idea,

519
00:30:44,401 --> 00:30:45,735
maybe he's...

520
00:30:47,696 --> 00:30:50,282
I don't know, I... I'm just
trying to make sense of this.

521
00:30:52,075 --> 00:30:53,493
And the poor man.

522
00:30:54,161 --> 00:30:56,496
He was shattered by
the Holy Father's death.

523
00:30:57,247 --> 00:30:58,290
Yes, indeed.

524
00:30:58,415 --> 00:31:00,458
Again, Joe, er, my apologies.

525
00:31:00,584 --> 00:31:01,960
No, not at all.

526
00:31:03,295 --> 00:31:05,130
I completely understand.

527
00:31:05,964 --> 00:31:06,965
(door opens)

528
00:31:07,090 --> 00:31:08,090
Erm...

529
00:31:08,842 --> 00:31:11,553
what did you discuss with
the Holy Father

530
00:31:11,678 --> 00:31:13,221
in that final meeting?

531
00:31:13,346 --> 00:31:14,723
Forgive me, Thomas.

532
00:31:15,891 --> 00:31:18,018
It was a private conversation,

533
00:31:18,143 --> 00:31:19,644
and very precious.

534
00:31:20,187 --> 00:31:22,230
Those were the last words
I ever exchanged

535
00:31:22,355 --> 00:31:23,773
with the Holy Father.

536
00:31:25,192 --> 00:31:26,234
Yes, of course.

537
00:31:28,153 --> 00:31:29,196
Goodnight, Joe.

538
00:31:30,238 --> 00:31:31,406
Goodnight Thomas.

539
00:31:32,449 --> 00:31:33,742
(footsteps receding)

540
00:31:36,995 --> 00:31:38,580
(door closes, locks)

541
00:31:40,415 --> 00:31:41,583
(dramatic music)

542
00:31:45,045 --> 00:31:46,296
- Decano.
- Ah!

543
00:31:48,548 --> 00:31:50,342
Oh, we're neighbours, Joshua.

544
00:31:50,884 --> 00:31:52,844
Ah, it appears so. (chuckles)

545
00:31:52,969 --> 00:31:55,347
I thought that I should, er...
(door beeps, opens)

546
00:31:55,472 --> 00:31:58,183
do a little more work on
my homily for tomorrow.

547
00:31:58,308 --> 00:32:00,727
Ah, yes, of course. I look forward to it.

548
00:32:00,852 --> 00:32:01,853
(Lawrence chuckles)

549
00:32:01,978 --> 00:32:03,021
I understand the trick

550
00:32:03,146 --> 00:32:04,856
is to offend no one.

551
00:32:04,981 --> 00:32:07,943
(both chuckling)

552
00:32:09,945 --> 00:32:12,739
(key clicks, beeping)
(door opens)

553
00:32:15,575 --> 00:32:16,618
(door closes)

554
00:32:26,419 --> 00:32:30,340
(cardinal chanting through wall)

555
00:32:32,759 --> 00:32:34,511
(toilet flushes)

556
00:32:45,397 --> 00:32:48,692
(soft music)
(packet rumples)

557
00:32:56,032 --> 00:32:59,119
(packet rips)
(clattering)

558
00:33:05,458 --> 00:33:07,002
You're a manager.

559
00:33:09,212 --> 00:33:10,422
Manage.

560
00:33:11,589 --> 00:33:13,091
(dramatic music)

561
00:33:22,017 --> 00:33:24,185
(choral music)
(church bells ring)

562
00:33:24,561 --> 00:33:25,895
BENITEZ: Decano Lawrence?

563
00:33:26,021 --> 00:33:27,856
(echoing, distorted chatter)

564
00:33:29,399 --> 00:33:31,776
(footsteps receding)

565
00:33:46,833 --> 00:33:50,211
(chain clanks)
(choral chanting)

566
00:34:52,065 --> 00:34:54,567
(book opens, pages turn)

567
00:35:02,367 --> 00:35:04,577
(in Italian): Dear Brothers in Christ,

568
00:35:06,162 --> 00:35:08,915
at the moment of great
uncertainty,

569
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:11,084
in the history of
the Holy Church,

570
00:35:11,418 --> 00:35:15,630
we must think first of
the late Holy Father,

571
00:35:16,381 --> 00:35:20,718
whose brilliant pontificate
was a gift from God,

572
00:35:21,386 --> 00:35:26,766
now we must ask our Lord to
send us a new Holy Father,

573
00:35:27,142 --> 00:35:31,980
through the pastoral solicitude
of the cardinal fathers.

574
00:35:33,148 --> 00:35:37,777
And we must pray to God for
that loving assistance,

575
00:35:38,319 --> 00:35:40,405
and ask Him to guide us

576
00:35:41,322 --> 00:35:44,617
to the right choice.

577
00:35:51,082 --> 00:35:52,709
(in English):
But you know all that.

578
00:35:54,878 --> 00:35:57,380
Let me speak from the heart for
a moment.

579
00:35:59,257 --> 00:36:02,010
St Paul said, 'Be subject to
one another

580
00:36:02,135 --> 00:36:04,345
out of reverence for Christ.'

581
00:36:05,430 --> 00:36:07,182
To work together, and to, er...

582
00:36:07,307 --> 00:36:10,727
to grow together,
we must be tolerant.

583
00:36:11,728 --> 00:36:15,607
No one person or... or faction
seeking to dominate another.

584
00:36:16,900 --> 00:36:18,651
And speaking to the Ephesians,

585
00:36:18,776 --> 00:36:22,113
who were of course a mixture of
Jews and gentiles,

586
00:36:22,614 --> 00:36:26,409
Paul reminds us that God's gift
to the church...

587
00:36:27,535 --> 00:36:29,370
is its variety.

588
00:36:29,496 --> 00:36:33,374
It is this variety, this diversity of
people and views

589
00:36:33,500 --> 00:36:37,003
which gives our church
its strength.

590
00:36:37,128 --> 00:36:38,408
And over the course of
many years

591
00:36:38,505 --> 00:36:40,173
in the service of our
Mother the Church,

592
00:36:40,298 --> 00:36:42,759
let me tell you, there is
one sin,

593
00:36:42,884 --> 00:36:45,720
which I have come to
fear above all others.

594
00:36:47,680 --> 00:36:48,973
Certainty.

595
00:36:50,475 --> 00:36:52,018
(someone clears his throat)

596
00:36:52,143 --> 00:36:54,687
Certainty is the great enemy of unity.

597
00:36:57,357 --> 00:37:00,735
Certainty is the deadly enemy
of tolerance.

598
00:37:03,404 --> 00:37:05,865
Even Christ was not certain
at the end.

599
00:37:05,990 --> 00:37:08,743
(in Italian): My God, My God, why are you
forsaken me?

600
00:37:08,868 --> 00:37:12,914
(in English): He cried out in his agony at the
ninth hour on the cross.

601
00:37:13,957 --> 00:37:16,084
Our faith is a living thing,

602
00:37:16,209 --> 00:37:19,921
precisely because it walks
hand-in-hand with doubt.

603
00:37:21,673 --> 00:37:23,258
If there was only certainty...

604
00:37:23,967 --> 00:37:25,009
and no doubt...

605
00:37:26,135 --> 00:37:28,054
there would be no mystery...

606
00:37:28,179 --> 00:37:29,389
(whispering)

607
00:37:29,514 --> 00:37:32,350
and therefore no need...
for faith.

608
00:37:35,395 --> 00:37:40,275
Let us pray that God will grant
us a Pope who doubts.

609
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:44,696
And let him grant us a Pope who
sins and asks for forgiveness,

610
00:37:45,780 --> 00:37:47,156
and who carries on.

611
00:37:55,832 --> 00:37:57,417
(sombre music)

612
00:38:04,924 --> 00:38:06,426
(quiet prayers uttered)

613
00:38:09,262 --> 00:38:10,471
(bell tolls)

614
00:38:28,489 --> 00:38:30,158
(ominous music)

615
00:38:47,175 --> 00:38:48,384
Dean Lawrence...

616
00:38:48,801 --> 00:38:52,096
your homily has
caused quite the stir.

617
00:38:52,221 --> 00:38:53,890
I don't think anyone expected
you to...

618
00:38:54,015 --> 00:38:55,600
To say something interesting?

619
00:38:58,978 --> 00:39:01,189
I'll have a transcript made of
the recording.

620
00:39:01,314 --> 00:39:02,314
Mm-hmm.

621
00:39:03,650 --> 00:39:06,819
If, erm, if there's nothing
else...

622
00:39:10,114 --> 00:39:11,449
Eminence.

623
00:39:11,574 --> 00:39:12,867
Yes, erm...

624
00:39:14,702 --> 00:39:16,829
I... I need you to do
something for me.

625
00:39:16,954 --> 00:39:18,748
Monsignor Morales...

626
00:39:18,873 --> 00:39:20,541
I'm sure he's still in Rome.

627
00:39:21,542 --> 00:39:22,669
Could you try and see him?

628
00:39:22,794 --> 00:39:25,004
- Today? I... I...
- Use my authority.

629
00:39:25,129 --> 00:39:26,714
I'd like to know what happened

630
00:39:26,839 --> 00:39:28,883
in the final meeting between
Cardinal Tremblay

631
00:39:29,008 --> 00:39:30,259
and the Holy Father.

632
00:39:31,552 --> 00:39:32,637
What happened?

633
00:39:32,762 --> 00:39:34,555
Specifically, did anything
occur that might

634
00:39:34,681 --> 00:39:37,767
render Tremblay unfit for
the Papacy?

635
00:39:42,855 --> 00:39:44,148
Of course, Your Eminence.

636
00:39:45,149 --> 00:39:46,149
Bless you.

637
00:39:48,277 --> 00:39:49,904
(footsteps receding)

638
00:39:54,117 --> 00:39:55,785
(slap)
(high tempo music)

639
00:40:17,890 --> 00:40:19,434
(security radio chatter)

640
00:40:23,438 --> 00:40:27,024
(in Latin): And I,
Irumbus Cardinal Nakitanda,

641
00:40:27,859 --> 00:40:32,655
I promise, I vow and I swear
so God will help me

642
00:40:33,114 --> 00:40:37,702
and these Holy Gospels of God,
which I touch with my hand.

643
00:40:37,827 --> 00:40:38,870
(cameras clicking)

644
00:40:53,843 --> 00:40:55,595
(tense music)

645
00:40:57,138 --> 00:40:59,015
Out, everyone.

646
00:41:00,016 --> 00:41:01,058
(loud clatter)

647
00:41:03,770 --> 00:41:04,937
(another loud clatter)

648
00:41:05,062 --> 00:41:06,564
(quiet chatter)

649
00:41:08,858 --> 00:41:10,401
(distant choral singing)

650
00:41:18,409 --> 00:41:19,869
(bell tolls)

651
00:41:24,123 --> 00:41:25,708
(bell tolls)

652
00:41:29,837 --> 00:41:31,631
(bell tolls)

653
00:41:35,343 --> 00:41:36,969
(bell tolls)

654
00:41:39,889 --> 00:41:42,266
(bell tolls)

655
00:41:42,391 --> 00:41:44,185
(quiet chatter)
(distant choral singing)

656
00:41:46,979 --> 00:41:47,980
(lock clicks)

657
00:41:51,192 --> 00:41:52,401
(doors click)

658
00:41:55,780 --> 00:41:57,824
(doors close with heavy bang)

659
00:41:57,949 --> 00:41:59,492
(locks click loudly)

660
00:42:16,759 --> 00:42:18,094
(in Italian): Cardinal brothers,

661
00:42:18,803 --> 00:42:21,806
we will now proceed to
the first ballot.

662
00:42:22,473 --> 00:42:26,227
You will find in front of you
your ballot paper.

663
00:42:26,769 --> 00:42:31,274
On the top half is written,
"I elect as Supreme Pontiff."

664
00:42:32,024 --> 00:42:36,153
Please make sure your
handwriting is legible.

665
00:42:44,745 --> 00:42:46,372
(quiet whispering)

666
00:42:48,499 --> 00:42:49,792
(papers rustling)

667
00:43:00,303 --> 00:43:01,971
(pens scratching on paper)

668
00:43:03,306 --> 00:43:04,640
(paper folds)

669
00:43:07,101 --> 00:43:11,063
(in Latin): I call as my witness Christ the Lord
who will be my judge

670
00:43:11,564 --> 00:43:15,318
that my vote is given to
the one who, before God,

671
00:43:15,443 --> 00:43:17,862
I think should be elected.

672
00:43:22,116 --> 00:43:23,576
(ballot clangs)
(lid clinks)

673
00:43:33,502 --> 00:43:34,795
(somebody coughs)

674
00:43:53,814 --> 00:43:56,943
(in Italian): The first vote
is cast for Cardinal Tedesco.

675
00:44:03,783 --> 00:44:07,536
The second vote is cast for
Cardinal Tedesco.

676
00:44:10,039 --> 00:44:11,415
Cardinal Tremblay.

677
00:44:15,252 --> 00:44:16,796
Cardinale Tremblay.

678
00:44:19,340 --> 00:44:20,800
Cardinale Tedesco.

679
00:44:23,427 --> 00:44:25,304
Cardinale Adeyemi.

680
00:44:28,224 --> 00:44:30,142
Cardinale Lawrence.

681
00:44:33,771 --> 00:44:35,856
Cardinale Bellini.

682
00:44:38,901 --> 00:44:40,778
Cardinale Bellini.

683
00:44:43,614 --> 00:44:45,491
Cardinale Villanueva.

684
00:44:47,576 --> 00:44:49,036
Cardinale Tremblay.

685
00:44:51,163 --> 00:44:52,832
Cardinale Adeyemi.

686
00:44:54,959 --> 00:44:56,585
Cardinale Tremblay.

687
00:44:57,920 --> 00:44:59,755
Cardinale Tedesco.

688
00:45:01,257 --> 00:45:03,342
Cardinale Bellini.

689
00:45:04,385 --> 00:45:06,387
Cardinale Adeyemi.

690
00:45:08,305 --> 00:45:11,350
And finally, Cardinal Benitez.

691
00:45:13,936 --> 00:45:18,607
The results of
the first ballot are...

692
00:45:19,108 --> 00:45:22,278
Cardinal Adeyemi, 21 votes.

693
00:45:23,446 --> 00:45:26,657
Cardinal Tedesco, 18 votes.

694
00:45:28,034 --> 00:45:31,245
Cardinal Bellini, 17 votes.

695
00:45:31,871 --> 00:45:34,749
Cardinal Tremblay, 16 votes.

696
00:45:35,583 --> 00:45:38,044
Cardinal Lawrence, 5 votes.

697
00:45:39,045 --> 00:45:44,050
Other cardinals assigned
a single vote, 31 votes

698
00:45:44,592 --> 00:45:45,968
(mumbling, chatter)

699
00:45:51,640 --> 00:45:53,267
(dramatic music)

700
00:45:58,064 --> 00:45:59,356
My brother cardinals,

701
00:45:59,482 --> 00:46:02,318
that concludes the first ballot.

702
00:46:03,027 --> 00:46:05,154
No candidate having achieved

703
00:46:05,279 --> 00:46:08,532
the necessary majority
of 72 votes,

704
00:46:08,866 --> 00:46:12,078
we shall adjourn for
the evening,

705
00:46:12,203 --> 00:46:15,372
and resume voting in
the morning.

706
00:46:16,082 --> 00:46:17,249
Thank you.

707
00:46:17,374 --> 00:46:19,335
(ominous music)

708
00:46:19,460 --> 00:46:20,461
(loud knocking on door)

709
00:46:22,296 --> 00:46:23,297
(doors clank open)

710
00:46:26,759 --> 00:46:27,843
(key turns)

711
00:46:28,719 --> 00:46:30,054
(button clicks)

712
00:46:30,179 --> 00:46:31,722
{\an8}(smoke hisses, billows)

713
00:46:37,394 --> 00:46:38,854
(crowd cheers)

714
00:46:46,028 --> 00:46:47,488
(high tempo music)

715
00:46:51,408 --> 00:46:53,553
(in English): The media have noticed the presence
of a cardinal

716
00:46:53,577 --> 00:46:55,377
who doesn't appear on
the official list, Dean,

717
00:46:55,454 --> 00:46:56,580
Cardinal Benitez.

718
00:46:56,705 --> 00:46:58,040
So, I've taken the liberty of

719
00:46:58,165 --> 00:46:59,917
putting together
a draft statement.

720
00:47:00,042 --> 00:47:02,044
I've also put together some biographical details

721
00:47:02,169 --> 00:47:03,254
for yourself.

722
00:47:03,379 --> 00:47:06,048
The ministries in Veracruz, the Congo,

723
00:47:06,423 --> 00:47:09,468
where he established a hospital
for the female victims

724
00:47:09,593 --> 00:47:11,554
of genocidal sexual violence

725
00:47:11,679 --> 00:47:13,764
during the first and second
wars.

726
00:47:13,889 --> 00:47:18,185
Then Baghdad, and finally, a mission in Kabul.

727
00:47:18,310 --> 00:47:19,770
Right.

728
00:47:19,895 --> 00:47:21,495
There was some question of his resigning

729
00:47:21,522 --> 00:47:22,606
on health grounds,

730
00:47:22,731 --> 00:47:23,931
but apparently the Holy Father

731
00:47:24,024 --> 00:47:25,276
convinced him to continue.

732
00:47:25,401 --> 00:47:26,721
He's certainly served his
ministry

733
00:47:26,819 --> 00:47:28,028
in some terrible places.

734
00:47:28,154 --> 00:47:29,989
- Yes.
- Health grounds.

735
00:47:30,406 --> 00:47:31,699
Look into that, would you, Ray?

736
00:47:31,824 --> 00:47:33,200
It's the kind of thing

737
00:47:33,325 --> 00:47:34,618
the press like to get hold of.

738
00:47:34,743 --> 00:47:35,870
Of course.

739
00:47:36,579 --> 00:47:39,707
And the, erm... other matter.
The...

740
00:47:41,125 --> 00:47:43,169
Yes.

741
00:47:43,294 --> 00:47:46,964
I spoke to Monsignor Morales.

742
00:47:47,089 --> 00:47:49,383
He was emphatic that he knows
of no reason why

743
00:47:49,508 --> 00:47:52,261
Cardinal Tremblay should not
be Pope.

744
00:47:54,388 --> 00:47:55,764
- Thank you.
- However...

745
00:47:56,140 --> 00:47:57,558
will you forgive me if I say...

746
00:47:58,267 --> 00:48:00,895
I did not entirely believe...

747
00:48:01,020 --> 00:48:02,354
the good monsignor?

748
00:48:02,479 --> 00:48:03,522
He was just...

749
00:48:04,315 --> 00:48:07,651
so... emphatic.

750
00:48:07,776 --> 00:48:09,195
My Spanish is quite poor

751
00:48:09,320 --> 00:48:12,615
and I may have accidentally
given him the impression

752
00:48:12,740 --> 00:48:15,242
that you had seen a document
that contradicts that.

753
00:48:15,367 --> 00:48:18,120
And he said you weren't
to worry,

754
00:48:18,245 --> 00:48:20,664
that... and his exact words were,

755
00:48:20,789 --> 00:48:22,750
'El informe ha sido retirado.'

756
00:48:22,875 --> 00:48:25,127
A report? A report about what?

757
00:48:25,878 --> 00:48:27,129
Withdrawn when?

758
00:48:27,254 --> 00:48:29,340
That... I couldn't say, Eminence.

759
00:48:29,465 --> 00:48:30,883
(treacherous music)

760
00:48:31,467 --> 00:48:32,467
Hmm.

761
00:48:33,052 --> 00:48:34,595
(people chattering)
(bell tolls)

762
00:48:36,597 --> 00:48:38,140
(angry exhale)

763
00:48:42,561 --> 00:48:44,605
(dramatic music)

764
00:48:44,730 --> 00:48:45,981
Third place.

765
00:48:46,565 --> 00:48:48,234
Not what we had hoped.

766
00:48:48,984 --> 00:48:51,487
Your sermon didn't exactly
help us and you have five votes.

767
00:48:51,904 --> 00:48:53,614
You have far too little support
to emerge

768
00:48:53,739 --> 00:48:54,907
as a serious candidate.

769
00:48:55,032 --> 00:48:56,718
Well, my position is an
embarrassment to me.

770
00:48:56,742 --> 00:48:58,494
If I find out who my
supporters are,

771
00:48:58,619 --> 00:49:00,537
I'll plead with them to
vote for someone else.

772
00:49:01,121 --> 00:49:03,082
I'll tell them I'll be voting
for Aldo.

773
00:49:03,207 --> 00:49:04,207
Alright.

774
00:49:05,417 --> 00:49:07,711
That leaves 31 votes available.

775
00:49:07,836 --> 00:49:09,546
We simply have to pick up most
of them.

776
00:49:12,091 --> 00:49:13,634
(squeaking)

777
00:49:13,759 --> 00:49:14,759
(dramatic music)

778
00:49:19,306 --> 00:49:20,683
(sirens blaring)

779
00:49:42,538 --> 00:49:44,164
LAWRENCE:
The Holy Father's turtles.

780
00:49:44,581 --> 00:49:46,083
He was very fond of them.

781
00:49:46,208 --> 00:49:48,252
A gift from Angola.
(water babbling)

782
00:49:48,377 --> 00:49:49,920
I thought I was imagining them.

783
00:49:50,045 --> 00:49:51,964
I love them. They're so clever.

784
00:49:52,089 --> 00:49:55,884
Well, here they keep escaping
and being run over. (chuckles)

785
00:49:56,010 --> 00:49:58,304
We should go back,
the evening curfew.

786
00:50:01,974 --> 00:50:04,184
And your health, how are you
bearing up?

787
00:50:04,893 --> 00:50:06,186
My health is perfect, thank you.

788
00:50:06,312 --> 00:50:09,106
I only meant have you recovered
from your journey?

789
00:50:09,231 --> 00:50:10,733
- I have, indeed.
- Good.

790
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:14,528
And in the Sistine, you found
someone to vote for?

791
00:50:15,154 --> 00:50:16,989
Yes. I voted for you.

792
00:50:18,741 --> 00:50:20,326
Forgive me, am I not
supposed to say?

793
00:50:20,451 --> 00:50:22,202
No, no, it's not that you...

794
00:50:22,536 --> 00:50:24,997
No, I'm honoured, but...
my dear Vincent,

795
00:50:25,122 --> 00:50:26,540
may I call you Vincent?

796
00:50:27,333 --> 00:50:29,084
I'm not a serious candidate.

797
00:50:30,044 --> 00:50:32,212
My vocation lies in
a different... um...

798
00:50:35,299 --> 00:50:38,302
After the Conclave, I hope to
resign as Dean,

799
00:50:38,427 --> 00:50:40,512
and then leave Rome altogether.

800
00:50:40,637 --> 00:50:41,637
Why?

801
00:50:47,269 --> 00:50:49,188
I've been experiencing
difficulties.

802
00:50:50,522 --> 00:50:51,522
With your faith?

803
00:50:56,236 --> 00:50:57,236
Prayer.

804
00:51:00,491 --> 00:51:02,117
I only mention it to illustrate
my point

805
00:51:02,493 --> 00:51:04,787
that I'm in no way
worthy to be Pope.

806
00:51:07,247 --> 00:51:08,247
Come.

807
00:51:11,168 --> 00:51:12,544
(intercom announcement)

808
00:51:14,421 --> 00:51:17,049
(metal clanging)

809
00:51:17,174 --> 00:51:18,884
(footsteps approaching)

810
00:51:20,344 --> 00:51:21,428
Aldo.

811
00:51:25,057 --> 00:51:26,057
Aldo.

812
00:51:28,977 --> 00:51:32,773
I... I feel wretched that my
...my meagre tally of votes

813
00:51:32,898 --> 00:51:34,817
may have come at your expense.

814
00:51:36,151 --> 00:51:37,194
Hmm.

815
00:51:37,903 --> 00:51:41,073
I had no idea you were
so ambitious.

816
00:51:41,198 --> 00:51:43,117
Well, that's a ridiculous thing
to say.

817
00:51:43,909 --> 00:51:44,909
Is it?

818
00:51:46,537 --> 00:51:47,537
Is it?

819
00:51:48,664 --> 00:51:50,082
I thought we had your support.

820
00:51:50,916 --> 00:51:54,461
If we liberals are not united,
Tedesco will become Pope.

821
00:51:55,129 --> 00:51:57,089
You have no idea how bad it
became, Thomas.

822
00:51:57,214 --> 00:51:59,174
The way he and his circle
attacked the Holy Father

823
00:51:59,216 --> 00:52:00,092
towards the end.

824
00:52:00,217 --> 00:52:01,009
The smears,

825
00:52:01,135 --> 00:52:02,261
the leaks to the press.

826
00:52:02,386 --> 00:52:03,846
It was savage.

827
00:52:03,971 --> 00:52:07,391
He fought him every single day of his pontificate.

828
00:52:07,975 --> 00:52:08,975
And now that he's dead,

829
00:52:09,059 --> 00:52:10,227
he wants to destroy

830
00:52:10,352 --> 00:52:11,478
his life's work.

831
00:52:12,646 --> 00:52:14,398
If Tedesco becomes Pope,

832
00:52:14,982 --> 00:52:18,110
he will undo 60 years
of progress.

833
00:52:18,235 --> 00:52:19,915
You talk as if you're
the only alternative,

834
00:52:20,154 --> 00:52:22,531
but Adeyemi has
the wind behind him.

835
00:52:22,656 --> 00:52:23,824
- Adeyemi?
- Mm-hmm.

836
00:52:23,949 --> 00:52:25,749
Adeyemi, the man who believes
that homosexuals

837
00:52:25,868 --> 00:52:27,388
should be sent to prison
in this world,

838
00:52:27,453 --> 00:52:28,704
and hell in the next.

839
00:52:29,371 --> 00:52:31,331
Adeyemi's not the answer
to anything.

840
00:52:31,457 --> 00:52:32,457
And you know it.

841
00:52:33,083 --> 00:52:34,363
If you want to defeat Tedesco...

842
00:52:34,418 --> 00:52:36,587
Defeat? This is a Conclave,
Aldo,

843
00:52:36,712 --> 00:52:39,131
- it's not a war.
- It is a war!

844
00:52:39,715 --> 00:52:42,718
And you have to commit
to a side.

845
00:52:48,182 --> 00:52:50,225
Save your precious doubts for
your prayers.

846
00:52:53,187 --> 00:52:54,605
You can't seriously believe

847
00:52:54,730 --> 00:52:57,816
that I have the slightest
desire to become Pope.

848
00:52:57,941 --> 00:52:58,942
Come on!

849
00:52:59,651 --> 00:53:01,361
Every cardinal has that desire.

850
00:53:01,737 --> 00:53:03,614
Every cardinal deep down has
already chosen

851
00:53:03,739 --> 00:53:05,991
the name by which he would like
his Papacy to be known.

852
00:53:06,116 --> 00:53:07,993
Well... I haven't.

853
00:53:08,494 --> 00:53:10,370
(scoffs) Deny it if you like,

854
00:53:11,163 --> 00:53:14,041
but search your heart and then
tell me it isn't so.

855
00:53:21,381 --> 00:53:22,841
(footsteps receding)

856
00:53:41,193 --> 00:53:42,569
(soft music)

857
00:53:51,453 --> 00:53:52,663
(groans)

858
00:54:05,926 --> 00:54:07,886
NUN: Oh, oh, Mother, an evil...

859
00:54:08,011 --> 00:54:09,346
(background chatter)

860
00:54:14,726 --> 00:54:16,436
(man and woman shouting
through walls)

861
00:54:19,439 --> 00:54:20,439
(click)

862
00:54:30,701 --> 00:54:32,119
(shouting grows louder)

863
00:54:34,496 --> 00:54:35,622
(door opens)

864
00:54:36,748 --> 00:54:37,874
(door slams loudly)

865
00:54:38,208 --> 00:54:39,251
(door opens)

866
00:54:39,751 --> 00:54:42,004
(footsteps receding)

867
00:54:55,767 --> 00:54:56,852
(door closes)

868
00:54:59,229 --> 00:55:01,356
(tense music)

869
00:55:01,481 --> 00:55:03,400
(quiet chatter)
(papers shuffling)

870
00:55:16,663 --> 00:55:20,626
(in Italian): The results
of the second ballot are...

871
00:55:21,126 --> 00:55:24,630
Cardinal Adeyemi, 34 votes.

872
00:55:26,131 --> 00:55:28,842
Cardinal Tedesco, 25 votes.

873
00:55:30,844 --> 00:55:33,680
Cardinal Bellini, 18 votes.

874
00:55:35,349 --> 00:55:38,602
Cardinal Tremblay, 16 votes.

875
00:55:39,353 --> 00:55:40,353
(furnace door closes)

876
00:55:40,520 --> 00:55:43,649
Cardinal Lawrence, 9 votes.

877
00:55:45,192 --> 00:55:47,778
Cardinal Benitez, 2 votes.

878
00:55:48,695 --> 00:55:49,946
(chatter, murmuring)

879
00:55:54,785 --> 00:55:59,665
My brothers, in accordance with
the Apostolic Constitution,

880
00:55:59,790 --> 00:56:03,710
we proceed immediately
to the next vote.

881
00:56:03,835 --> 00:56:04,836
Thank you.

882
00:56:08,465 --> 00:56:09,966
(ballot clangs)

883
00:56:10,092 --> 00:56:11,092
(lid clinks)

884
00:56:12,886 --> 00:56:16,598
The results of
the third ballot are...

885
00:56:17,057 --> 00:56:20,811
Cardinal Adeyemi, 52 votes.

886
00:56:22,354 --> 00:56:24,940
Cardinal Tedesco, 30 votes.

887
00:56:25,857 --> 00:56:28,318
Cardinal Tremblay, 10 votes.

888
00:56:29,653 --> 00:56:30,821
Cardinal Bellini...

889
00:56:30,946 --> 00:56:32,114
(rumbling)

890
00:56:34,741 --> 00:56:35,992
(loud chatter)

891
00:56:44,292 --> 00:56:45,292
Brothers.

892
00:56:45,877 --> 00:56:46,877
Please.

893
00:56:48,130 --> 00:56:49,130
Thank you.

894
00:56:51,633 --> 00:56:54,511
Cardinal Bellini, 9 votes.

895
00:56:55,637 --> 00:56:58,223
Cardinal Lawrence, 5 votes.

896
00:56:59,391 --> 00:57:02,394
Cardinal Benitez, 4 votes.

897
00:57:02,811 --> 00:57:04,187
(siren blaring distantly)

898
00:57:05,063 --> 00:57:06,231
(birds tweeting)

899
00:57:10,694 --> 00:57:12,279
(siren grows louder)
(nuns chattering)

900
00:57:20,579 --> 00:57:22,598
(in English): Well, I take it
something has happened.

901
00:57:22,622 --> 00:57:24,183
There's been an explosion, Your Eminence,

902
00:57:24,207 --> 00:57:25,542
in the Piazza Barberini.

903
00:57:25,667 --> 00:57:28,211
- A bomb?
- It's unclear at the moment.

904
00:57:28,336 --> 00:57:30,881
There are injuries, but no talk
of fatalities.

905
00:57:32,174 --> 00:57:33,550
We must say nothing to
the cardinal

906
00:57:33,675 --> 00:57:34,801
electors about this, Ray.

907
00:57:34,926 --> 00:57:36,136
We are sequestered,

908
00:57:36,470 --> 00:57:38,388
and they must be shielded
from all news

909
00:57:38,513 --> 00:57:40,098
that may influence
their judgement.

910
00:57:40,766 --> 00:57:42,726
- You understand?
- Of course, Your Eminence.

911
00:57:45,562 --> 00:57:47,272
(footsteps receding)

912
00:57:47,397 --> 00:57:48,857
(dark music)

913
00:57:50,442 --> 00:57:52,027
(loud chatter)

914
00:57:55,030 --> 00:57:56,323
This is exactly what I mean.

915
00:57:56,448 --> 00:57:58,116
What am I supposed to tell them in Milan

916
00:57:58,617 --> 00:58:02,454
when they start to discover our
new Pope's social views?

917
00:58:03,246 --> 00:58:05,582
Tell your congregation that
they should celebrate

918
00:58:05,707 --> 00:58:09,127
the first African Pope in
the history of the church.

919
00:58:10,003 --> 00:58:12,005
If Adeyemi was white,

920
00:58:12,714 --> 00:58:14,132
we would be all condemning him

921
00:58:14,257 --> 00:58:16,134
as more reactionary
than Tedesco?

922
00:58:16,259 --> 00:58:17,445
It's only because he's
not white...

923
00:58:17,469 --> 00:58:19,262
It's too late for all that.

924
00:58:19,387 --> 00:58:20,180
It's too late.

925
00:58:20,305 --> 00:58:21,305
(men shouting angrily)

926
00:58:21,348 --> 00:58:22,557
(clattering)

927
00:58:23,934 --> 00:58:25,519
(chair scrapes)
(woman sobs)

928
00:58:25,644 --> 00:58:27,395
(footsteps receding)

929
00:58:29,231 --> 00:58:30,357
What happened?

930
00:58:32,943 --> 00:58:34,903
(clattering, clanging)
(steam hissing)

931
00:58:42,160 --> 00:58:43,203
(sharp rapping on door)

932
00:58:49,668 --> 00:58:51,753
(door opens)
Good afternoon, Sister.

933
00:58:51,878 --> 00:58:54,840
I would like to speak to the nun
who dropped her tray just now.

934
00:58:54,965 --> 00:58:56,943
She's safe with me, I'm dealing
with the situation, Dean.

935
00:58:56,967 --> 00:59:00,387
I'm sure you are, Sister Agnes,
but I must see her myself.

936
00:59:00,512 --> 00:59:02,514
I hardly think a dropped tray should concern

937
00:59:02,639 --> 00:59:04,683
the Dean of the College
of Cardinals.

938
00:59:04,808 --> 00:59:05,809
Even so, I...

939
00:59:05,934 --> 00:59:07,102
The welfare of the sister

940
00:59:07,227 --> 00:59:08,436
is my responsibility.

941
00:59:08,562 --> 00:59:10,605
And this Conclave is mine.

942
00:59:13,900 --> 00:59:15,569
(bird tweets)
(door opens)

943
00:59:19,322 --> 00:59:20,322
(door closes)

944
00:59:22,075 --> 00:59:23,952
Please sit, my child.

945
00:59:27,038 --> 00:59:29,583
My name is Cardinal Lawrence.

946
00:59:29,708 --> 00:59:30,750
How are you feeling?

947
00:59:30,876 --> 00:59:32,002
She's feeling much better.

948
00:59:32,127 --> 00:59:33,628
Could you tell me your name?

949
00:59:34,045 --> 00:59:35,839
Shanumi, her name is Shanumi.

950
00:59:35,964 --> 00:59:37,883
Please, please do sit down.

951
00:59:38,008 --> 00:59:39,360
I... I really think it would
be better

952
00:59:39,384 --> 00:59:40,927
if you let me deal with
the situation.

953
00:59:41,052 --> 00:59:43,847
Would you be so good as to
leave us now, Sister Agnes?

954
00:59:51,021 --> 00:59:52,981
(footsteps receding)

955
00:59:53,106 --> 00:59:54,106
(door opens)

956
00:59:56,318 --> 00:59:57,318
(door closes)

957
00:59:59,112 --> 01:00:00,822
(chair trundles)

958
01:00:06,786 --> 01:00:08,163
Sister Shanumi,

959
01:00:09,623 --> 01:00:11,458
I want you to understand that,
first of all,

960
01:00:11,583 --> 01:00:14,169
you are not in any
kind of trouble.

961
01:00:14,294 --> 01:00:16,004
The fact of the matter is that I have

962
01:00:16,129 --> 01:00:17,756
a responsibility before God

963
01:00:17,881 --> 01:00:20,759
to ensure that the decisions
that we make here

964
01:00:21,343 --> 01:00:22,719
are the right ones.

965
01:00:24,179 --> 01:00:27,599
Now, it's important you tell me
anything that is in your heart

966
01:00:27,724 --> 01:00:29,017
or that is troubling you,

967
01:00:29,142 --> 01:00:32,729
insofar as it relates to
Cardinal Adeyemi.

968
01:00:34,522 --> 01:00:35,315
(bird tweets)

969
01:00:35,440 --> 01:00:36,650
Can you do that for me?

970
01:00:41,321 --> 01:00:43,031
Even if I give you my assurance

971
01:00:43,156 --> 01:00:45,450
it will go no further than
this room.

972
01:00:58,880 --> 01:01:01,633
Would you like me to hear your
confession?

973
01:01:05,887 --> 01:01:07,472
(knocking loudly)

974
01:01:07,597 --> 01:01:08,890
(footsteps approaching)

975
01:01:10,725 --> 01:01:13,061
(door opens)

976
01:01:13,186 --> 01:01:14,562
I'll be ready in a moment, Dean.

977
01:01:16,314 --> 01:01:17,816
(footsteps receding)

978
01:01:23,488 --> 01:01:24,948
(door closes, locks)

979
01:01:25,448 --> 01:01:27,617
(tap running)
(footsteps approaching)

980
01:01:38,086 --> 01:01:39,166
(Adeyemi clears his throat)

981
01:01:44,426 --> 01:01:45,218
Shouldn't we be going?

982
01:01:45,343 --> 01:01:46,720
In a moment.

983
01:01:46,845 --> 01:01:47,887
That sounds ominous.

984
01:01:53,685 --> 01:01:55,285
If this is about the incident
downstairs,

985
01:01:55,353 --> 01:01:56,896
I have no desire to
talk about it.

986
01:01:59,858 --> 01:02:00,858
(sighs)

987
01:02:01,192 --> 01:02:03,278
I am the victim of
a disgraceful plot

988
01:02:03,403 --> 01:02:04,946
to ruin my reputation.

989
01:02:05,321 --> 01:02:08,825
Someone brought that woman here
and staged this melodrama.

990
01:02:09,159 --> 01:02:10,493
She'd never left Nigeria before,

991
01:02:10,618 --> 01:02:12,996
and suddenly she's here
in the Casa Santa Marta.

992
01:02:13,121 --> 01:02:14,998
With respect, Joshua,
ow she came here

993
01:02:15,123 --> 01:02:16,458
is secondary to the issue

994
01:02:16,583 --> 01:02:18,209
of your relationship with her.

995
01:02:18,334 --> 01:02:21,004
I have no relationship to her!

996
01:02:22,839 --> 01:02:24,591
I hadn't set eyes on her
in 30 years

997
01:02:24,716 --> 01:02:26,676
until she turned up
outside my room last night!

998
01:02:28,053 --> 01:02:29,053
(frustrated sigh)

999
01:02:33,058 --> 01:02:34,517
It was a lapse, Dean.

1000
01:02:36,394 --> 01:02:37,394
A lapse.

1001
01:02:39,481 --> 01:02:42,942
'Let God grant us a Pope who
sins and asks forgiveness

1002
01:02:43,068 --> 01:02:44,152
and carries on.'

1003
01:02:44,277 --> 01:02:45,820
- Your words.
- And the child?

1004
01:02:46,738 --> 01:02:47,738
The child?

1005
01:02:49,282 --> 01:02:50,575
(scoffs)

1006
01:02:57,207 --> 01:02:59,542
The child was raised in
a Christian household,

1007
01:02:59,667 --> 01:03:01,878
and to this day he has no idea
who his father is,

1008
01:03:02,003 --> 01:03:03,421
if, indeed, it is me.

1009
01:03:04,714 --> 01:03:05,965
That is the child.

1010
01:03:08,176 --> 01:03:09,886
We were very young.

1011
01:03:10,011 --> 01:03:11,679
No, no, no, Joshua,

1012
01:03:11,805 --> 01:03:14,974
she was very young,
she was 19 years old.

1013
01:03:15,100 --> 01:03:16,559
- You were 30.
- Thomas.

1014
01:03:17,519 --> 01:03:18,519
Thomas.

1015
01:03:19,020 --> 01:03:20,897
Listen to me... please.

1016
01:03:23,775 --> 01:03:25,902
I sensed the presence of
the Holy Spirit this morning,

1017
01:03:26,027 --> 01:03:27,027
I swear it.

1018
01:03:28,780 --> 01:03:30,490
I am ready to take this burden.

1019
01:03:32,158 --> 01:03:34,994
Do... does a single...
single mistake 30 years ago

1020
01:03:35,120 --> 01:03:36,329
disqualify me?

1021
01:03:38,581 --> 01:03:40,375
Thomas, please, I was
a different man.

1022
01:03:42,961 --> 01:03:45,338
Please, I... I beg you, do... do
not use this to ruin me.

1023
01:03:45,463 --> 01:03:47,465
Joshua, that thought's not
worthy of you.

1024
01:03:47,590 --> 01:03:50,260
Shanumi will say nothing to
protect her son,

1025
01:03:50,885 --> 01:03:53,304
and I am bound
by the vows of the confessional.

1026
01:03:55,223 --> 01:03:56,724
(Adeyemi exhales)

1027
01:03:56,850 --> 01:03:57,851
So, I still have hope?

1028
01:03:58,685 --> 01:03:59,685
No.

1029
01:04:03,815 --> 01:04:05,525
There is no hope.

1030
01:04:06,734 --> 01:04:08,629
After such a public scene,
there will be rumours,

1031
01:04:08,653 --> 01:04:10,864
and you know
what the Curia is like.

1032
01:04:10,989 --> 01:04:12,574
Nothing terrifies our colleagues more

1033
01:04:12,699 --> 01:04:16,786
than the thought of yet more...
sexual scandals.

1034
01:04:18,913 --> 01:04:21,082
I am more sorry than I can say.

1035
01:04:23,334 --> 01:04:24,627
You will never be Pope.

1036
01:04:24,752 --> 01:04:26,087
(sobs)

1037
01:04:29,883 --> 01:04:31,301
You must begin again.

1038
01:04:34,179 --> 01:04:36,598
But you are a good man.

1039
01:04:36,723 --> 01:04:37,765
(sobbing)

1040
01:04:38,850 --> 01:04:40,685
I know you to be a good man,

1041
01:04:41,019 --> 01:04:43,104
and you will find a way
to atone.

1042
01:04:44,981 --> 01:04:46,441
(sobbing)

1043
01:05:04,209 --> 01:05:06,753
ADEYEMI: Will you pray with me?
(sobs)

1044
01:05:08,254 --> 01:05:09,088
(sombre music)

1045
01:05:09,214 --> 01:05:10,506
Yes, of course.

1046
01:05:15,428 --> 01:05:16,763
(sobbing)

1047
01:05:37,283 --> 01:05:38,326
(sobbing)

1048
01:05:59,097 --> 01:06:00,390
(urn clangs)

1049
01:06:26,499 --> 01:06:28,167
(tense music)

1050
01:06:28,668 --> 01:06:32,213
(in Italian): The results of
the fifth ballot are...

1051
01:06:33,673 --> 01:06:36,509
Cardinal Tremblay, 40 votes.

1052
01:06:37,927 --> 01:06:40,763
Cardinal Tedesco, 34 votes.

1053
01:06:42,473 --> 01:06:45,268
Cardinal Bellini, 13 votes.

1054
01:06:47,228 --> 01:06:49,897
Cardinal Lawrence, 11 votes.

1055
01:06:51,816 --> 01:06:54,736
Cardinal Adeyemi, 9 votes.

1056
01:06:55,945 --> 01:06:58,865
Cardinal Benitez, 6 votes.

1057
01:06:59,741 --> 01:07:00,908
(loud murmuring)

1058
01:07:01,784 --> 01:07:02,869
My brothers...

1059
01:07:03,911 --> 01:07:06,331
My brothers, that concludes
the fifth ballot.

1060
01:07:07,290 --> 01:07:10,585
No candidate having achieved
the necessary majority,

1061
01:07:11,210 --> 01:07:13,880
we shall resume voting
tomorrow morning.

1062
01:07:27,352 --> 01:07:28,353
(clears throat)

1063
01:07:29,187 --> 01:07:30,187
(in English): Yes, Ray?

1064
01:07:30,855 --> 01:07:33,566
The... incident this morning,
Your Eminence.

1065
01:07:33,691 --> 01:07:35,443
I have more information, if...

1066
01:07:35,568 --> 01:07:38,071
No, I too must be shielded from
any knowledge

1067
01:07:38,196 --> 01:07:40,198
which could act as
an interference

1068
01:07:40,323 --> 01:07:42,033
in the process of this Conclave.

1069
01:07:42,158 --> 01:07:43,409
Of course, Your Eminence.

1070
01:07:44,452 --> 01:07:45,452
Anything else?

1071
01:07:45,495 --> 01:07:46,496
Erm...

1072
01:07:46,913 --> 01:07:49,999
Oh, Cardinal Benitez...
who has health problems?

1073
01:07:50,375 --> 01:07:52,585
He was issued a round-trip
ticket to Geneva

1074
01:07:52,710 --> 01:07:56,255
paid for by
the Pope's own account.

1075
01:07:56,381 --> 01:07:58,383
I checked his visa application,

1076
01:07:58,508 --> 01:08:01,803
the purpose for travel was
given as 'medical treatment'.

1077
01:08:01,928 --> 01:08:05,640
Anyway, whatever it was,
it can't have been serious.

1078
01:08:05,765 --> 01:08:07,325
The ticket was cancelled,
he never went.

1079
01:08:07,392 --> 01:08:09,018
Alright. Thank you.

1080
01:08:17,151 --> 01:08:18,611
Forgive me, Your Eminence.

1081
01:08:19,862 --> 01:08:22,990
I know you said we should
forget about the matter

1082
01:08:23,116 --> 01:08:25,576
of the withdrawn report.

1083
01:08:25,701 --> 01:08:27,370
But I... I wondered...

1084
01:08:27,954 --> 01:08:31,958
in light of Cardinal Tremblay's
current position...

1085
01:08:33,418 --> 01:08:35,670
I... I could see if I could
find out...

1086
01:08:35,795 --> 01:08:37,380
No, I'm not a witch-finder.

1087
01:08:37,755 --> 01:08:39,507
It's not my job to go hunting
for secrets

1088
01:08:39,632 --> 01:08:40,967
in my colleagues' pasts.

1089
01:08:46,806 --> 01:08:47,806
Forgive me.

1090
01:08:49,600 --> 01:08:51,769
Please, no more investigations,
I...

1091
01:08:53,729 --> 01:08:55,273
I think we've heard enough
secrets.

1092
01:09:00,736 --> 01:09:02,238
Let God's will be done.

1093
01:09:03,573 --> 01:09:04,657
Yes, of course.

1094
01:09:05,241 --> 01:09:06,534
Goodnight then, Your Eminence.

1095
01:09:07,368 --> 01:09:08,870
(footsteps recede)

1096
01:09:23,593 --> 01:09:24,593
(knock on door)

1097
01:09:29,515 --> 01:09:30,725
Was this really necessary?

1098
01:09:30,850 --> 01:09:32,602
I feel as if I'm at some

1099
01:09:32,727 --> 01:09:34,729
American political convention.

1100
01:09:35,104 --> 01:09:37,231
Well, it isn't going to
take long.

1101
01:09:37,356 --> 01:09:39,734
Our friend here doesn't have sufficient support

1102
01:09:39,859 --> 01:09:41,819
amongst our colleagues to be
elected Pope.

1103
01:09:41,944 --> 01:09:42,944
It isn't over yet.

1104
01:09:43,029 --> 01:09:43,905
Well, I'm afraid,

1105
01:09:44,030 --> 01:09:45,656
as far as I'm concerned, it is.

1106
01:09:47,575 --> 01:09:49,869
So, now the question arises,

1107
01:09:49,994 --> 01:09:51,579
if I can't win,

1108
01:09:52,455 --> 01:09:55,750
whom do I advise
my supporters to vote for?

1109
01:09:58,503 --> 01:09:59,503
Thomas,

1110
01:09:59,545 --> 01:10:01,088
I am no more an enthusiast

1111
01:10:01,214 --> 01:10:02,798
for Tremblay than you are.

1112
01:10:03,549 --> 01:10:06,093
But... we have to face the fact
that...

1113
01:10:06,219 --> 01:10:08,596
(clanging, gate squeaks open)

1114
01:10:08,971 --> 01:10:10,890
(footsteps echoing)

1115
01:10:15,811 --> 01:10:16,979
(door opens)

1116
01:10:18,231 --> 01:10:19,315
(door closes)

1117
01:10:19,440 --> 01:10:21,317
We have to face the fact

1118
01:10:21,442 --> 01:10:23,653
that he has demonstrated broad
appeal.

1119
01:10:25,571 --> 01:10:27,782
Maybe he'll be a unifying force.

1120
01:10:28,449 --> 01:10:30,368
- What?
- Is this what we're reduced to,

1121
01:10:30,493 --> 01:10:34,497
considering the least
worst option?

1122
01:10:34,622 --> 01:10:36,123
But the field has narrowed.

1123
01:10:36,749 --> 01:10:39,293
If we don't change our vote,
we will be here for weeks.

1124
01:10:39,418 --> 01:10:41,546
And that's exactly what
Tedesco wants.

1125
01:10:41,671 --> 01:10:43,589
We've had a Pope who was
in the Hitler Youth

1126
01:10:43,714 --> 01:10:44,924
and fought for the Nazis.

1127
01:10:45,049 --> 01:10:46,342
We've had Popes accused of

1128
01:10:46,467 --> 01:10:49,011
colluding with communists
and fascists.

1129
01:10:49,136 --> 01:10:51,138
We've had Popes who have
ignored reports

1130
01:10:51,264 --> 01:10:53,391
of most appalling sexual abuse
of children!

1131
01:10:53,516 --> 01:10:54,934
Shh. Okay. Shh-shh!

1132
01:10:56,060 --> 01:10:57,144
We take the point.

1133
01:10:57,270 --> 01:11:00,231
The point is we will never
find a candidate

1134
01:11:00,356 --> 01:11:03,734
who doesn't have any kind of
black mark against them.

1135
01:11:03,859 --> 01:11:05,820
We're mortal men.

1136
01:11:05,945 --> 01:11:07,280
We serve an ideal.

1137
01:11:08,239 --> 01:11:10,366
We cannot always be ideal.

1138
01:11:17,331 --> 01:11:18,374
Then we're agreed.

1139
01:11:19,333 --> 01:11:22,378
We urge all our supporters to
back Tremblay.

1140
01:11:24,463 --> 01:11:25,463
Good.

1141
01:11:26,215 --> 01:11:29,719
(footsteps receding)
(door opens)

1142
01:11:33,931 --> 01:11:35,975
The other night, you were
kind enough

1143
01:11:36,100 --> 01:11:38,060
to say that
you had voted for me.

1144
01:11:39,186 --> 01:11:41,230
Now, I don't know if you've
continued to do so,

1145
01:11:41,355 --> 01:11:45,610
but if you have, then I must
repeat my plea to you to stop.

1146
01:11:47,111 --> 01:11:48,112
Why?

1147
01:11:48,487 --> 01:11:51,115
Well, firstly, I lack the
spiritual depth

1148
01:11:51,240 --> 01:11:52,283
to be Pope.

1149
01:11:53,159 --> 01:11:55,161
Secondly,
I couldn't possibly win.

1150
01:11:55,661 --> 01:11:57,121
A long, drawn-out Conclave

1151
01:11:57,246 --> 01:11:59,206
would be seen by the media
as proof

1152
01:11:59,332 --> 01:12:01,584
that the Church is in crisis.

1153
01:12:01,709 --> 01:12:03,961
You have come to ask me to vote
for Cardinal Tremblay?

1154
01:12:04,086 --> 01:12:06,964
Yes, I have, and to urge your
supporters to do the same.

1155
01:12:07,590 --> 01:12:09,800
Cardinal Tremblay already spoke
to me about this.

1156
01:12:09,925 --> 01:12:11,385
Oh, well, I'm sure he has.

1157
01:12:11,761 --> 01:12:14,597
You want me to vote for a man
you see as ambitious?

1158
01:12:16,682 --> 01:12:19,435
I do not want to see Tedesco
as Pope.

1159
01:12:20,061 --> 01:12:23,272
He would take our church back
to... to an earlier era.

1160
01:12:23,606 --> 01:12:25,816
I'm sorry, but I cannot vote
for a man

1161
01:12:25,941 --> 01:12:28,527
unless I deem him
the most worthy to be Pope.

1162
01:12:29,111 --> 01:12:31,530
And for me, that is not
Tremblay.

1163
01:12:32,323 --> 01:12:33,323
It's you.

1164
01:12:34,200 --> 01:12:36,535
I don't want your vote!

1165
01:12:36,661 --> 01:12:39,121
Nevertheless... you have it.

1166
01:12:45,419 --> 01:12:46,419
(blows softly)

1167
01:12:47,463 --> 01:12:48,923
(footsteps recede)

1168
01:12:49,048 --> 01:12:50,633
(tense, high tempo music)

1169
01:13:12,238 --> 01:13:15,116
Sister Shanumi is on her way
home to Nigeria.

1170
01:13:16,158 --> 01:13:18,536
There was a flight to Lagos
this evening,

1171
01:13:18,661 --> 01:13:21,747
and I thought it was best for
everyone if she was on it.

1172
01:13:22,456 --> 01:13:25,126
How did Sister Shanumi come to
be in Rome?

1173
01:13:25,960 --> 01:13:28,254
I received notification from
the office

1174
01:13:28,379 --> 01:13:31,632
of the Superioress General that
she would be joining us.

1175
01:13:32,299 --> 01:13:34,301
The arrangements were made
in Paris.

1176
01:13:34,427 --> 01:13:35,928
You should Rue de Bac,
Your Eminence.

1177
01:13:36,053 --> 01:13:37,680
I would, except of course, I am

1178
01:13:37,805 --> 01:13:40,266
sequestered for the duration of
the Conclave.

1179
01:13:40,975 --> 01:13:42,435
Then you should ask them
afterwards.

1180
01:13:44,270 --> 01:13:47,606
Err, the information is of value
to me now.

1181
01:13:52,486 --> 01:13:55,322
Sister Agnes, I know that you
were close to the Holy Father.

1182
01:13:56,407 --> 01:13:58,993
When I tried to resign as Dean,
he wouldn't let me.

1183
01:14:00,536 --> 01:14:03,247
I couldn't understand why at
the time, but...

1184
01:14:03,372 --> 01:14:05,040
now I think I do.

1185
01:14:07,168 --> 01:14:09,420
I think the Holy Father knew
he was dying,

1186
01:14:09,545 --> 01:14:14,592
and for some reason he wanted me
to run this Conclave.

1187
01:14:14,717 --> 01:14:16,927
Which is what I'm trying to do.

1188
01:14:20,347 --> 01:14:21,347
For him.

1189
01:14:36,405 --> 01:14:37,865
(taps on keyboard)

1190
01:14:48,292 --> 01:14:49,585
(door opens)

1191
01:14:51,545 --> 01:14:53,339
(door closes)

1192
01:14:53,464 --> 01:14:54,673
(bird twittering)

1193
01:14:56,342 --> 01:14:57,551
(chair trundles)

1194
01:15:05,351 --> 01:15:06,811
(mouse clicking)

1195
01:15:18,364 --> 01:15:19,532
(dark music)

1196
01:15:19,657 --> 01:15:21,325
I would like you to withdraw
your name

1197
01:15:21,450 --> 01:15:22,493
from the next ballot.

1198
01:15:23,077 --> 01:15:24,161
(laughs)

1199
01:15:24,286 --> 01:15:26,080
You are not the right man
to be Pope.

1200
01:15:26,831 --> 01:15:27,915
Er, well...

1201
01:15:28,040 --> 01:15:29,041
40 of our colleagues

1202
01:15:29,166 --> 01:15:30,393
would disagree with you on that.

1203
01:15:30,417 --> 01:15:32,503
That's because they don't know
you as I do.

1204
01:15:34,588 --> 01:15:36,048
This is sad, Thomas.

1205
01:15:37,466 --> 01:15:38,843
I shall pray for you.

1206
01:15:38,968 --> 01:15:40,261
I know there was some kind of

1207
01:15:40,386 --> 01:15:41,720
report into your activities.

1208
01:15:42,304 --> 01:15:44,264
I know the Holy Father raised the matter with you

1209
01:15:44,306 --> 01:15:45,349
hours before he died.

1210
01:15:45,474 --> 01:15:47,518
And that he dismissed you
from all your posts.

1211
01:15:47,643 --> 01:15:49,645
And I know that somehow
you discovered

1212
01:15:49,770 --> 01:15:52,731
Adeyemi's surrender to
temptation 30 years ago,

1213
01:15:52,857 --> 01:15:54,692
and that you arranged for
the woman involved

1214
01:15:54,817 --> 01:15:55,860
to be brought to Rome,

1215
01:15:55,985 --> 01:15:57,111
with the express intention

1216
01:15:57,236 --> 01:15:59,196
of destroying Adeyemi's chances

1217
01:15:59,321 --> 01:16:00,321
of becoming Pope.

1218
01:16:00,364 --> 01:16:01,615
I deny that accusation.

1219
01:16:01,740 --> 01:16:04,493
Will you deny asking our
Superioress to transfer

1220
01:16:04,618 --> 01:16:05,995
one of her sisters to Rome?

1221
01:16:06,120 --> 01:16:08,455
- No. I asked her.
- Hmm.

1222
01:16:08,581 --> 01:16:10,821
- But not on my own behalf.
- Well, on whose behalf then?

1223
01:16:10,916 --> 01:16:12,126
The Holy Father's.

1224
01:16:12,251 --> 01:16:14,628
You would libel the Holy Father in his own home?

1225
01:16:14,753 --> 01:16:17,756
It isn't libel, it's the truth!

1226
01:16:18,549 --> 01:16:20,926
The Holy Father gave me
the name of a sister

1227
01:16:21,051 --> 01:16:24,263
and asked me to make a private
request to bring her to Rome.

1228
01:16:24,763 --> 01:16:26,390
I have no idea why.

1229
01:16:26,515 --> 01:16:28,475
And now you have chosen to...

1230
01:16:29,643 --> 01:16:30,978
(sinister music)

1231
01:16:32,313 --> 01:16:33,939
You should be careful, Thomas.

1232
01:16:36,317 --> 01:16:39,320
Your own ambition has not
gone unnoticed.

1233
01:16:40,321 --> 01:16:44,450
This might be seen as a tactic
to blacken the name of a rival.

1234
01:16:44,575 --> 01:16:46,201
Well, that's a despicable
accusation.

1235
01:16:46,327 --> 01:16:47,327
Is it?

1236
01:16:48,412 --> 01:16:49,412
I wonder...

1237
01:16:50,789 --> 01:16:54,335
if you really are so
very reluctant

1238
01:16:54,460 --> 01:16:56,962
to have the chalice
passed to you.

1239
01:17:01,926 --> 01:17:04,970
I shall pretend this
conversation never took place.

1240
01:17:06,013 --> 01:17:07,598
(sinister music continues)

1241
01:17:07,723 --> 01:17:09,683
(footsteps recede)

1242
01:17:10,225 --> 01:17:11,727
But it has taken place!

1243
01:17:16,482 --> 01:17:17,524
(sinister beat)

1244
01:17:21,612 --> 01:17:22,988
(sinister beat repeated)

1245
01:17:23,113 --> 01:17:24,113
(bell chimes)

1246
01:17:29,203 --> 01:17:30,329
(intercom announcement)

1247
01:17:31,956 --> 01:17:33,749
(Lawrence breathes heavily)

1248
01:17:48,222 --> 01:17:50,057
(sinister, high tempo music)

1249
01:17:56,814 --> 01:17:58,649
(music grows in intensity)

1250
01:17:58,774 --> 01:18:00,943
(snapping)

1251
01:18:03,821 --> 01:18:05,030
(ribbon pulling)

1252
01:18:12,913 --> 01:18:13,956
(door closes)

1253
01:18:18,460 --> 01:18:19,460
(light switch clicks)

1254
01:18:26,885 --> 01:18:28,846
(sinister music)
(drawer opens)

1255
01:18:37,187 --> 01:18:38,647
(drawer closes)

1256
01:18:48,449 --> 01:18:49,575
(clasp clicks)

1257
01:19:00,961 --> 01:19:02,546
(pill bottle rattles)

1258
01:19:12,306 --> 01:19:13,599
(book flips open)

1259
01:19:21,190 --> 01:19:22,566
(mutters)

1260
01:19:24,777 --> 01:19:26,153
(intercom announcement repeats)

1261
01:19:35,954 --> 01:19:37,164
(slight gasp)

1262
01:19:38,123 --> 01:19:39,458
(treacherous music)

1263
01:19:42,377 --> 01:19:44,171
(fearful breathing)

1264
01:19:47,466 --> 01:19:48,967
(high tempo music)

1265
01:20:01,271 --> 01:20:03,065
(treacherous music)

1266
01:20:23,961 --> 01:20:25,504
(door rattles)
(high tempo beat)

1267
01:20:33,137 --> 01:20:34,304
(sinister music)

1268
01:20:37,474 --> 01:20:38,809
(footsteps receding)

1269
01:20:46,316 --> 01:20:47,442
(door opens)

1270
01:20:53,031 --> 01:20:54,032
(light switch clicks)

1271
01:20:58,078 --> 01:20:59,371
(wardrobe doors open)

1272
01:21:05,836 --> 01:21:07,254
(deep sigh)

1273
01:21:08,672 --> 01:21:09,882
(wardrobe doors close)

1274
01:21:20,142 --> 01:21:23,145
(footsteps pacing)

1275
01:21:50,380 --> 01:21:51,715
(sobbing)

1276
01:22:03,143 --> 01:22:04,519
(sobbing grows louder)

1277
01:22:15,906 --> 01:22:17,574
(uninhibited crying)

1278
01:22:41,390 --> 01:22:42,849
(treacherous beat)

1279
01:22:54,278 --> 01:22:55,654
(rattling)

1280
01:22:57,197 --> 01:22:58,197
(click)

1281
01:23:06,873 --> 01:23:08,792
(ominous music continues)

1282
01:23:26,184 --> 01:23:28,395
LAWRENCE: It's the report on
the activities of Tremblay.

1283
01:23:28,520 --> 01:23:31,481
It's an overwhelming prima
facie case that he is guilty

1284
01:23:31,606 --> 01:23:33,817
of simony, which, of course,
is an offence stipulated

1285
01:23:33,942 --> 01:23:35,837
- in the Holy Scriptures...
- I'm aware of what simony is,

1286
01:23:35,861 --> 01:23:36,981
- thank you.
- He only obtained

1287
01:23:37,070 --> 01:23:38,423
all those votes
in the first ballot

1288
01:23:38,447 --> 01:23:39,614
because he bought them.

1289
01:23:40,574 --> 01:23:43,535
Cardenas, Diene, Figarella,
Baptiste...

1290
01:23:44,661 --> 01:23:46,330
And all this in the last twelve months

1291
01:23:46,455 --> 01:23:48,248
when he must have
guessed the Holy Father's

1292
01:23:48,373 --> 01:23:50,292
pontificate was... was coming
to an end.

1293
01:23:50,417 --> 01:23:52,210
How do we know that this money
wasn't used

1294
01:23:52,336 --> 01:23:54,463
for completely
legitimate purposes?

1295
01:23:54,588 --> 01:23:56,590
Because I have seen their bank
statements.

1296
01:23:59,301 --> 01:24:00,661
- Dear God.
- Seems the Holy Father

1297
01:24:00,719 --> 01:24:02,346
was spying on all of us.

1298
01:24:04,389 --> 01:24:05,640
He didn't trust anyone.

1299
01:24:07,434 --> 01:24:08,727
Where did you get this?

1300
01:24:10,771 --> 01:24:11,855
You broke the seals.

1301
01:24:11,980 --> 01:24:13,440
I felt I didn't have a choice.

1302
01:24:13,565 --> 01:24:15,192
I suspected Tremblay of bringing

1303
01:24:15,317 --> 01:24:18,320
that poor woman from
Africa to embarrass Adeyemi.

1304
01:24:18,737 --> 01:24:21,573
You must continue with your
candidacy, Aldo.

1305
01:24:21,698 --> 01:24:22,908
(papers rustle)

1306
01:24:27,371 --> 01:24:28,371
Put them back.

1307
01:24:30,248 --> 01:24:35,045
Put them back, or burn them,
or... just... put them back.

1308
01:24:35,504 --> 01:24:37,798
I could never become Pope in
these circumstances.

1309
01:24:37,923 --> 01:24:40,342
A stolen document, the smearing
of a brother cardinal.

1310
01:24:40,467 --> 01:24:42,427
I'd be the
Richard Nixon of Popes.

1311
01:24:42,552 --> 01:24:44,179
Then stay clear of this,
leave it to me.

1312
01:24:44,304 --> 01:24:46,014
I'm willing to handle
the consequences.

1313
01:24:46,139 --> 01:24:47,974
You know who's gonna benefit
most from this?

1314
01:24:48,850 --> 01:24:50,602
Tedesco.

1315
01:24:50,727 --> 01:24:52,604
The whole basis of his candidacy

1316
01:24:52,729 --> 01:24:56,024
is that the Holy Father
led the church to disaster

1317
01:24:56,149 --> 01:24:57,859
by his attempts at reform.

1318
01:24:57,984 --> 01:24:59,778
If you reveal this report,

1319
01:25:00,445 --> 01:25:02,614
it isn't Tremblay's reputation
that's going to suffer,

1320
01:25:03,073 --> 01:25:04,157
it's the Church's.

1321
01:25:05,409 --> 01:25:09,079
Accusing the Curia of
institutional corruption...

1322
01:25:09,204 --> 01:25:12,582
I thought we were here to serve
God, not the Curia.

1323
01:25:12,707 --> 01:25:14,251
Oh, don't be naïve!

1324
01:25:17,504 --> 01:25:18,504
(sighs)

1325
01:25:19,714 --> 01:25:20,715
Put them back.

1326
01:25:23,343 --> 01:25:25,387
And have Tremblay as Pope?

1327
01:25:25,512 --> 01:25:26,596
We've had worse.

1328
01:25:26,721 --> 01:25:27,721
(door opens)

1329
01:25:32,727 --> 01:25:33,770
What has he offered you?

1330
01:25:35,814 --> 01:25:37,232
Secretary of State?

1331
01:25:43,572 --> 01:25:47,075
Five times I cast my vote
for you, Aldo.

1332
01:25:48,785 --> 01:25:49,953
But I was wrong.

1333
01:25:51,496 --> 01:25:53,874
You lack the courage required
to be Pope.

1334
01:25:58,295 --> 01:25:59,588
(door opens)

1335
01:26:01,298 --> 01:26:02,924
(door closes)
(shutters whirring)

1336
01:26:06,136 --> 01:26:07,136
(beep)

1337
01:26:08,889 --> 01:26:09,889
(sighs)

1338
01:26:09,973 --> 01:26:11,016
(dark, high tempo music)

1339
01:26:11,475 --> 01:26:13,518
SISTER AGNES: I will do that
for you, Your Eminence

1340
01:26:14,394 --> 01:26:15,479
Oh.

1341
01:26:16,271 --> 01:26:17,271
(lid creaks open)

1342
01:26:18,690 --> 01:26:19,690
(lid bangs shut)

1343
01:26:21,026 --> 01:26:22,736
How many copies do you require?

1344
01:26:23,403 --> 01:26:24,905
Er, 108.

1345
01:26:29,618 --> 01:26:30,994
(copier whirring)

1346
01:26:39,002 --> 01:26:40,795
(music intensity rises)

1347
01:26:43,840 --> 01:26:46,218
You are responsible for this,
I believe.

1348
01:26:46,343 --> 01:26:47,343
(chatter)

1349
01:26:47,385 --> 01:26:49,262
No, Eminence. You are.

1350
01:26:49,387 --> 01:26:50,514
(sudden silence)

1351
01:26:50,847 --> 01:26:54,684
This report is entirely
mendacious.

1352
01:26:54,809 --> 01:26:56,478
It would never have seen
the light of day

1353
01:26:56,603 --> 01:26:58,355
if you had not broken into

1354
01:26:58,480 --> 01:27:00,607
the Holy Father's apartment to
remove it!

1355
01:27:00,732 --> 01:27:01,983
If the report is mendacious,

1356
01:27:02,108 --> 01:27:03,568
then why did the Holy Father

1357
01:27:03,693 --> 01:27:05,570
in his last official act as Pope

1358
01:27:05,695 --> 01:27:06,863
ask you to resign?

1359
01:27:06,988 --> 01:27:08,406
He did no such thing.

1360
01:27:08,907 --> 01:27:11,188
(stammers) As Monsignor Morales,
who was at the meeting...

1361
01:27:11,451 --> 01:27:14,120
And yet Archbishop Wozniak
insists the Holy Father...

1362
01:27:14,246 --> 01:27:15,246
The Holy Father,

1363
01:27:15,288 --> 01:27:16,540
may his name be numbered

1364
01:27:16,665 --> 01:27:17,832
among the high priests,

1365
01:27:17,958 --> 01:27:21,628
was a sick man toward
the end of his life,

1366
01:27:22,087 --> 01:27:25,757
as those of us who saw him
regularly can attest.

1367
01:27:25,882 --> 01:27:27,217
(laughter)

1368
01:27:27,551 --> 01:27:30,136
(in Italian): If I may join
this amiable dialogue.

1369
01:27:30,262 --> 01:27:31,680
I want to remind you that

1370
01:27:31,805 --> 01:27:35,267
the names of eight cardinals
have been obscured.

1371
01:27:37,435 --> 01:27:39,688
I assume the dean can tell us
who they are?

1372
01:27:39,813 --> 01:27:41,398
Let them tell us themselves

1373
01:27:41,773 --> 01:27:42,941
here and now.

1374
01:27:43,525 --> 01:27:44,943
Here and now!

1375
01:27:45,068 --> 01:27:47,612
(in English): If Cardinal Tremblay
requested their votes

1376
01:27:47,737 --> 01:27:49,030
in return for the money...

1377
01:27:49,155 --> 01:27:50,515
(in Italian): No, I won't do that.

1378
01:27:50,574 --> 01:27:51,950
(cardinals shouting)

1379
01:27:52,075 --> 01:27:55,495
(in English): Let each man examine his
conscience, as I have.

1380
01:27:56,454 --> 01:28:00,250
I have no desire to create
bitterness in this Conclave,

1381
01:28:00,375 --> 01:28:03,044
and I will be happy to stand
down as Dean.

1382
01:28:03,169 --> 01:28:04,754
(loud, clamorous shouting)

1383
01:28:15,473 --> 01:28:17,642
(room grows quiet)
(helicopter whirrs outside)

1384
01:28:17,767 --> 01:28:18,767
Eminences.

1385
01:28:19,978 --> 01:28:22,772
Although we sisters are
supposed to be invisible,

1386
01:28:22,897 --> 01:28:27,527
God has nevertheless given us
eyes and ears.

1387
01:28:27,652 --> 01:28:29,613
I know what prompted the Dean
of the College

1388
01:28:29,738 --> 01:28:33,158
to enter
the Holy Father's rooms.

1389
01:28:33,283 --> 01:28:35,619
He was concerned that
the sister from my order

1390
01:28:35,744 --> 01:28:38,496
that made that regrettable scene

1391
01:28:38,622 --> 01:28:40,457
might have been brought to Rome

1392
01:28:40,582 --> 01:28:42,667
with the deliberate intention

1393
01:28:43,251 --> 01:28:46,004
of embarrassing a member of
this Conclave.

1394
01:28:47,172 --> 01:28:49,049
His suspicions were correct.

1395
01:28:50,425 --> 01:28:52,927
She was indeed here at
the specific request

1396
01:28:53,053 --> 01:28:54,554
of Cardinal Tremblay.

1397
01:28:54,679 --> 01:28:56,765
(stunned silence)

1398
01:29:03,355 --> 01:29:04,606
(footsteps receding)

1399
01:29:14,032 --> 01:29:15,032
My brothers...

1400
01:29:16,409 --> 01:29:17,409
it's true.

1401
01:29:18,620 --> 01:29:21,581
But the Holy Father asked me to.

1402
01:29:23,208 --> 01:29:25,960
I had no knowledge

1403
01:29:26,086 --> 01:29:28,129
who this woman was,
I swear to you.

1404
01:29:33,510 --> 01:29:34,594
(in Italian): Judas.

1405
01:29:35,178 --> 01:29:36,388
Traitor.

1406
01:29:38,139 --> 01:29:39,808
(footsteps receding)

1407
01:29:39,933 --> 01:29:41,476
(quiet whispering)

1408
01:29:54,698 --> 01:29:56,032
(footsteps approaching)

1409
01:30:07,377 --> 01:30:09,737
(in English): It seems that
we're running out of favourites.

1410
01:30:13,591 --> 01:30:15,343
You must take over
the supervision

1411
01:30:15,468 --> 01:30:16,845
of this election, Aldo.

1412
01:30:18,388 --> 01:30:19,472
Oh, no thank you.

1413
01:30:19,848 --> 01:30:20,849
(laughs ironically)

1414
01:30:22,183 --> 01:30:24,018
You are steering this Conclave.

1415
01:30:25,687 --> 01:30:28,022
Exactly where, I do not know.

1416
01:30:28,982 --> 01:30:31,860
But that firm hand of yours
has its admirers.

1417
01:30:37,824 --> 01:30:41,035
Thomas I've come to ask...
for your forgiveness.

1418
01:30:45,373 --> 01:30:47,000
I had the temerity...

1419
01:30:47,959 --> 01:30:51,588
to tell you to examine...
your heart,

1420
01:30:51,713 --> 01:30:53,798
when all the time it was
my own that...

1421
01:31:00,180 --> 01:31:01,389
It's shameful...

1422
01:31:03,641 --> 01:31:07,061
to be this age
and still not know yourself.

1423
01:31:07,187 --> 01:31:10,064
Ambition, 'The moth of
holiness.'

1424
01:31:14,194 --> 01:31:15,320
I'm sorry.

1425
01:31:20,200 --> 01:31:24,120
So, perhaps it's time you
decided... upon a name.

1426
01:31:26,831 --> 01:31:28,958
As the next most senior member
of this Conclave,

1427
01:31:29,083 --> 01:31:30,752
it will fall to me to ask you

1428
01:31:30,877 --> 01:31:32,670
how you wish to be known
as Pope.

1429
01:31:35,548 --> 01:31:36,883
For better or for worse,

1430
01:31:37,008 --> 01:31:38,718
it would seem that Tremblay
is finished.

1431
01:31:41,179 --> 01:31:43,348
This is a contest between
Tedesco and you.

1432
01:31:43,765 --> 01:31:45,517
You're the only one who can
stop him now.

1433
01:31:53,733 --> 01:31:54,733
John.

1434
01:31:56,694 --> 01:31:58,196
I would choose John.

1435
01:31:59,531 --> 01:32:01,074
(soft music)

1436
01:32:11,459 --> 01:32:13,002
(breathing heavily)

1437
01:32:45,201 --> 01:32:46,619
(pen scratches)

1438
01:33:31,998 --> 01:33:33,207
(urn lid clinks)

1439
01:33:33,917 --> 01:33:36,544
(ballot clangs)
(deafening blast)

1440
01:33:36,669 --> 01:33:38,338
(shouting)

1441
01:33:38,463 --> 01:33:40,048
(rubble crashing)

1442
01:33:48,222 --> 01:33:49,766
(dramatic music)

1443
01:33:56,731 --> 01:33:58,316
(laboured breathing)

1444
01:34:30,765 --> 01:34:32,600
(footsteps approaching)

1445
01:34:34,185 --> 01:34:35,412
O'MALLEY: Everyone has been taken back

1446
01:34:35,436 --> 01:34:36,562
to the Casa Santa Marta,

1447
01:34:36,688 --> 01:34:37,772
Your Eminence.

1448
01:34:37,897 --> 01:34:38,937
No one was seriously hurt.

1449
01:34:38,982 --> 01:34:40,108
Some cuts, that's all.

1450
01:34:41,693 --> 01:34:44,153
Outside in the city,
how bad is it?

1451
01:34:58,167 --> 01:34:59,335
Oh, dear God.

1452
01:35:03,965 --> 01:35:06,300
At 11:20 this morning,

1453
01:35:06,801 --> 01:35:10,722
a car bomb exploded in
the Piazza del Risorgimento.

1454
01:35:11,055 --> 01:35:14,267
Shortly afterwards, as people
were fleeing the scene,

1455
01:35:14,851 --> 01:35:17,770
an individual with explosives
strapped to his body

1456
01:35:17,895 --> 01:35:19,355
detonated himself.

1457
01:35:19,856 --> 01:35:23,818
There are reports of further
attacks in Louvain and Munich.

1458
01:35:24,861 --> 01:35:26,863
The current death toll stands...

1459
01:35:28,114 --> 01:35:29,198
at 52.

1460
01:35:29,323 --> 01:35:30,450
(murmuring)

1461
01:35:30,908 --> 01:35:32,535
Hundreds have been injured.

1462
01:35:33,536 --> 01:35:34,536
(in Italian): Well, then.

1463
01:35:34,954 --> 01:35:39,542
Here at last we see the result of
the doctrine of relativism

1464
01:35:39,667 --> 01:35:42,920
so beloved by our liberal
brothers!

1465
01:35:44,881 --> 01:35:49,302
A relativism that sees all
faiths and passing fancies

1466
01:35:49,719 --> 01:35:51,554
accorded equal weight.

1467
01:35:51,679 --> 01:35:53,890
So that now, when we look
around us, we see the homeland

1468
01:35:54,015 --> 01:35:55,808
of the Holy Roman
Catholic Church

1469
01:35:56,601 --> 01:35:59,312
dotted with the mosques
and minarets

1470
01:35:59,437 --> 01:36:00,563
of the prophet Muhammad!

1471
01:36:00,688 --> 01:36:02,166
(in English): You should be ashamed ashamed.

1472
01:36:02,190 --> 01:36:03,190
Ashamed. Ashamed.

1473
01:36:03,274 --> 01:36:04,901
We should all be ashamed!

1474
01:36:05,026 --> 01:36:09,113
(in Italian): We tolerate Islam in our land,

1475
01:36:09,489 --> 01:36:10,990
but they revile us in theirs.

1476
01:36:11,115 --> 01:36:14,410
We nourish them
in our homelands.

1477
01:36:15,328 --> 01:36:16,662
But they exterminate us.

1478
01:36:16,788 --> 01:36:19,832
How long will we persist in
this weakness?

1479
01:36:19,957 --> 01:36:22,502
They are literally at our walls
right now.

1480
01:36:22,627 --> 01:36:25,838
What we need now is a leader
who understands

1481
01:36:25,963 --> 01:36:29,717
that we are facing
a true religious war.

1482
01:36:30,051 --> 01:36:31,385
Do not touch me!

1483
01:36:33,137 --> 01:36:34,847
Yes, a religious war.

1484
01:36:34,972 --> 01:36:37,892
We need a leader who will
put a stop to the drift

1485
01:36:38,017 --> 01:36:40,895
that has gone on almost ceaselessly
for the past 50 years.

1486
01:36:41,020 --> 01:36:43,189
How long will we have to
persist in this weakness,

1487
01:36:43,314 --> 01:36:44,314
how long?

1488
01:36:44,357 --> 01:36:46,400
We need a leader...

1489
01:36:46,859 --> 01:36:49,112
(in English):...who fights these animals!

1490
01:36:49,237 --> 01:36:50,947
(loud chatter)

1491
01:36:55,159 --> 01:36:57,411
CARDINAL: Is this the man you
want to lead us?

1492
01:37:01,582 --> 01:37:03,000
My brother cardinal...

1493
01:37:03,126 --> 01:37:04,585
(room falls silent)

1494
01:37:10,091 --> 01:37:11,551
With respect.

1495
01:37:13,761 --> 01:37:15,263
What do you know about war?

1496
01:37:18,933 --> 01:37:21,769
I carried out my ministry
in the Congo.

1497
01:37:21,894 --> 01:37:23,688
In Baghdad, in Kabul.

1498
01:37:25,606 --> 01:37:28,442
I've seen the lines of the dead
and wondered,

1499
01:37:28,568 --> 01:37:30,403
Christian and Muslim.

1500
01:37:33,906 --> 01:37:36,159
Would you say we have to fight?

1501
01:37:37,535 --> 01:37:39,328
What is it you think
we're fighting?

1502
01:37:40,830 --> 01:37:42,206
Do you think it's those
deluded men

1503
01:37:42,331 --> 01:37:45,209
who had carried out these
terrible acts today?

1504
01:37:46,711 --> 01:37:47,753
No, my brother.

1505
01:37:48,713 --> 01:37:50,713
(in Spanish): The thing you're fighting is here...

1506
01:37:52,300 --> 01:37:54,051
inside each and every one of us,

1507
01:37:54,760 --> 01:37:57,096
if we give in to hate now,

1508
01:37:58,848 --> 01:38:00,433
if we speak of "sides"

1509
01:38:00,558 --> 01:38:03,352
instead of speaking
for every man and woman.

1510
01:38:05,688 --> 01:38:07,940
This is my first time here, amongst you,

1511
01:38:08,399 --> 01:38:10,276
and I suppose it will be my last.

1512
01:38:12,695 --> 01:38:17,909
Forgive me, but these last few days
we have shown ourselves to be small petty men,

1513
01:38:20,161 --> 01:38:22,455
we have seemed concerned
only with ourselves,

1514
01:38:23,956 --> 01:38:24,956
with Rome,

1515
01:38:25,416 --> 01:38:27,168
with these elections, with power.

1516
01:38:29,503 --> 01:38:31,380
But things are not the Church.

1517
01:38:33,466 --> 01:38:35,134
The Church is not tradition.

1518
01:38:36,219 --> 01:38:37,929
The Church is not the past.

1519
01:38:40,473 --> 01:38:43,017
The Church is what we do next.

1520
01:38:43,517 --> 01:38:44,602
(dramatic music)

1521
01:38:55,863 --> 01:38:58,157
(dramatic, high tempo music)

1522
01:39:03,621 --> 01:39:04,997
(quiet chatter)

1523
01:39:37,989 --> 01:39:39,198
(dramatic music continues)

1524
01:39:50,209 --> 01:39:52,086
(rain falling)

1525
01:40:17,278 --> 01:40:18,446
(in Latin): We pray.

1526
01:40:18,571 --> 01:40:22,700
O Father, so that we may guide

1527
01:40:22,825 --> 01:40:26,245
and watch over Your Church.

1528
01:40:26,370 --> 01:40:28,080
Give to us, Your servants,

1529
01:40:28,205 --> 01:40:31,917
the blessings of intelligence,
truth and peace,

1530
01:40:32,335 --> 01:40:36,589
so that we may strive to know
Your will,

1531
01:40:36,714 --> 01:40:40,676
and serve You total dedication.

1532
01:40:43,679 --> 01:40:45,598
For Christ our Lord.

1533
01:40:45,723 --> 01:40:47,016
ALL: Amen.

1534
01:41:06,660 --> 01:41:08,371
(breeze blowing softly)

1535
01:41:31,602 --> 01:41:33,854
(ballots rustling)
(pens scratching)

1536
01:41:42,488 --> 01:41:43,823
(tense, dramatic music)

1537
01:41:50,746 --> 01:41:52,456
(quiet whispering)

1538
01:42:20,818 --> 01:42:22,069
Bellini.

1539
01:42:27,741 --> 01:42:29,368
Lawrence.

1540
01:42:32,413 --> 01:42:33,747
Tedesco.

1541
01:42:35,958 --> 01:42:37,334
Lawrence.

1542
01:42:43,799 --> 01:42:45,634
(applause)

1543
01:43:33,182 --> 01:43:34,808
(room falls silent)
(dramatic beat)

1544
01:43:36,435 --> 01:43:41,732
(in Italian): Do you accept your canonical
election as Supreme Pontiff?

1545
01:43:50,324 --> 01:43:56,205
Do you accept your canonical
election as Supreme Pontiff?

1546
01:44:03,754 --> 01:44:04,754
I accept.

1547
01:44:04,838 --> 01:44:05,923
(gasps, sighs)

1548
01:44:07,841 --> 01:44:10,052
And by what name do you
wish to be called?

1549
01:44:15,182 --> 01:44:16,600
Innocent.

1550
01:44:19,937 --> 01:44:21,480
(whispering)

1551
01:44:24,817 --> 01:44:26,944
(resounding applause)

1552
01:44:46,171 --> 01:44:48,173
(faint choral singing)

1553
01:44:49,842 --> 01:44:51,302
Monsignor.

1554
01:44:51,635 --> 01:44:53,804
(in English): I'm sorry to interrupt.

1555
01:44:54,805 --> 01:44:55,805
Ray...

1556
01:44:58,267 --> 01:45:00,477
I think you should gather
up the cardinals' notes.

1557
01:45:00,603 --> 01:45:01,854
The sooner we light the stove,

1558
01:45:01,979 --> 01:45:03,179
the sooner the world will know

1559
01:45:03,230 --> 01:45:04,315
we have a new Pope.

1560
01:45:07,401 --> 01:45:08,444
What is it?

1561
01:45:10,529 --> 01:45:11,572
It wasn't...

1562
01:45:12,531 --> 01:45:14,366
wasn't the outcome I expected.

1563
01:45:14,491 --> 01:45:16,452
No, but it's wonderful
all the same.

1564
01:45:18,537 --> 01:45:20,015
If it's my position you're
worried about,

1565
01:45:20,039 --> 01:45:22,416
I can reassure you I feel
nothing but relief.

1566
01:45:23,584 --> 01:45:25,669
Our new Holy Father will make
a much better Pope

1567
01:45:25,794 --> 01:45:27,296
than I would ever have done.

1568
01:45:33,636 --> 01:45:36,430
I wonder if I could have a word
in private.

1569
01:45:39,016 --> 01:45:41,560
I should have told you this
morning when I found out, but...

1570
01:45:42,645 --> 01:45:43,645
with everything that...

1571
01:45:43,687 --> 01:45:45,648
And I didn't dream

1572
01:45:45,773 --> 01:45:47,650
that Cardinal Benitez would
become...

1573
01:45:47,775 --> 01:45:50,194
Ray, please, tell me what's
troubling you.

1574
01:45:53,155 --> 01:45:54,323
I found out...

1575
01:45:55,282 --> 01:45:56,282
Switzerland.

1576
01:45:57,159 --> 01:45:59,286
Cardinal Benitez's trip
to Switzerland.

1577
01:45:59,411 --> 01:46:02,289
Switzerland, the... the hospital
in Geneva, yes?

1578
01:46:04,166 --> 01:46:05,626
It wasn't a hospital.

1579
01:46:06,418 --> 01:46:07,586
It was a clinic.

1580
01:46:10,756 --> 01:46:12,132
A clinic for what?

1581
01:46:14,468 --> 01:46:16,136
(chatter)

1582
01:46:22,017 --> 01:46:23,769
(rapping hard on door)

1583
01:46:24,687 --> 01:46:25,687
(door opens)

1584
01:46:25,771 --> 01:46:28,065
(in Italian): Eminence,
His Holiness won't get robed.

1585
01:46:28,190 --> 01:46:29,190
With permission.

1586
01:46:34,822 --> 01:46:36,448
(in English): May I speak to you alone?

1587
01:46:36,573 --> 01:46:37,573
{\an8}Of course.

1588
01:46:37,658 --> 01:46:39,498
(in Italian): Gentlemen, let's clear the room.

1589
01:46:39,660 --> 01:46:41,620
(footsteps receding)

1590
01:46:41,745 --> 01:46:42,745
(heavy doors close)

1591
01:46:47,042 --> 01:46:49,002
(in English): I was waiting for you to come.

1592
01:46:49,128 --> 01:46:50,838
You must tell me about
this treatment

1593
01:46:50,963 --> 01:46:52,548
at the clinic in Geneva.

1594
01:46:54,091 --> 01:46:55,759
- Must I, Dean?
- Yes, you must.

1595
01:46:56,510 --> 01:46:59,179
Within the hour you will be the
most famous man in the world,

1596
01:46:59,304 --> 01:47:03,809
so please tell me,
what is your... situation?

1597
01:47:05,769 --> 01:47:07,771
My situation, as you put it,

1598
01:47:08,647 --> 01:47:11,066
is the same as when I was
ordained a priest,

1599
01:47:12,151 --> 01:47:14,069
and when I was made a cardinal.

1600
01:47:14,194 --> 01:47:16,405
But the treatment... in Geneva?

1601
01:47:16,530 --> 01:47:17,948
There was no treatment.

1602
01:47:18,741 --> 01:47:20,200
I considered it.

1603
01:47:20,325 --> 01:47:22,536
I prayed for guidance and decided against it.

1604
01:47:22,661 --> 01:47:24,997
But what would it have been,
this treatment?

1605
01:47:27,541 --> 01:47:30,961
It was called a laparoscopic
hysterectomy.

1606
01:47:44,683 --> 01:47:46,351
(footsteps pacing)

1607
01:48:04,495 --> 01:48:06,371
(long, deep sigh)

1608
01:48:17,925 --> 01:48:19,551
You have to understand,

1609
01:48:21,720 --> 01:48:25,265
when I was a child, there was
no way of knowing my situation

1610
01:48:25,390 --> 01:48:26,850
was more complicated.

1611
01:48:28,769 --> 01:48:30,938
And life in the seminary is...

1612
01:48:31,063 --> 01:48:32,189
as you know,

1613
01:48:32,314 --> 01:48:33,816
a very modest one.

1614
01:48:36,401 --> 01:48:37,653
The truth is...

1615
01:48:37,986 --> 01:48:39,446
there simply was no reason
to think

1616
01:48:39,571 --> 01:48:40,611
I was physically different

1617
01:48:40,697 --> 01:48:41,949
from the other young men.

1618
01:48:43,534 --> 01:48:45,661
Then, in my late 30s,

1619
01:48:46,620 --> 01:48:50,165
I had a surgery to remove
my appendix.

1620
01:48:51,792 --> 01:48:54,002
And that was when the doctors
discovered...

1621
01:48:54,962 --> 01:48:58,382
that I had a uterus...
and ovaries.

1622
01:48:59,758 --> 01:49:01,093
Some would say

1623
01:49:01,218 --> 01:49:04,471
my chromosomes would define
me as being a woman,

1624
01:49:05,722 --> 01:49:07,224
and yet I'm also...

1625
01:49:08,100 --> 01:49:09,268
as you see me.

1626
01:49:20,821 --> 01:49:23,198
It was a very dark time for me.

1627
01:49:23,323 --> 01:49:25,284
I felt as if my entire life as a priest

1628
01:49:25,409 --> 01:49:27,536
had been lived in
a state of sin.

1629
01:49:29,329 --> 01:49:32,332
Of course, I offered my
resignation to the Holy Father.

1630
01:49:32,833 --> 01:49:35,085
I flew to Rome and I told him
everything.

1631
01:49:37,754 --> 01:49:38,839
He knew?

1632
01:49:40,340 --> 01:49:42,885
Yes, he knew.

1633
01:49:43,010 --> 01:49:44,928
And he thought it acceptable
for you

1634
01:49:45,053 --> 01:49:47,764
to continue as
an ordained minister?

1635
01:49:49,016 --> 01:49:52,644
We considered surgery to remove
the female parts of my body,

1636
01:49:52,769 --> 01:49:55,397
but the night before I was due
to fly,

1637
01:49:55,522 --> 01:49:57,441
I realised I was mistaken.

1638
01:49:58,692 --> 01:50:00,903
I was who I had always been.

1639
01:50:03,363 --> 01:50:04,990
It seemed to me more of a sin

1640
01:50:05,115 --> 01:50:08,410
to change His handiwork than
to leave my body as it was.

1641
01:50:11,121 --> 01:50:13,874
So, you are still, erm...

1642
01:50:15,918 --> 01:50:17,586
I am what God made me.

1643
01:50:19,546 --> 01:50:23,550
And perhaps it is my difference
that will make me more useful.

1644
01:50:26,053 --> 01:50:27,804
I think again of your sermon.

1645
01:50:30,182 --> 01:50:33,185
I know what it is to exist...

1646
01:50:33,310 --> 01:50:35,771
between the world's certainties.

1647
01:50:51,495 --> 01:50:53,455
(distant choral music)

1648
01:51:25,904 --> 01:51:27,114
(clanging)

1649
01:51:29,074 --> 01:51:30,575
(lighter flicks)
(flame flares)

1650
01:51:31,410 --> 01:51:32,452
(switch clicks)

1651
01:51:33,412 --> 01:51:34,496
(button clicks)

1652
01:51:35,789 --> 01:51:37,290
(loud murmuring)

1653
01:51:38,917 --> 01:51:40,127
(whoosh)

1654
01:51:44,381 --> 01:51:46,299
(footsteps crunching)

1655
01:51:51,596 --> 01:51:52,889
(water babbling gently)

1656
01:51:55,267 --> 01:51:56,810
(distant choral music)

1657
01:51:57,310 --> 01:51:59,688
(uproarious cheering, applause)

1658
01:52:11,575 --> 01:52:13,035
(pensive music)

1659
01:52:17,831 --> 01:52:18,999
(crowd cheering distantly)

1660
01:52:42,814 --> 01:52:44,107
(click, shutters whirring)

1661
01:52:52,157 --> 01:52:53,158
(distant talking)

1662
01:52:56,453 --> 01:52:57,453
Hmm.

1663
01:52:59,831 --> 01:53:01,291
(curtain swishes)

1664
01:53:01,708 --> 01:53:02,709
(window handle rattles)

1665
01:53:02,834 --> 01:53:04,044
(ambient street sounds)

1666
01:53:20,977 --> 01:53:22,562
(nuns chattering)

1667
01:53:40,038 --> 01:53:41,038
(window squeaks closed)

